3
00:00:10,070 --> 00:00:15,070
<i> <b><font size=35 color=#D6D6D7>{\fnSimHei}双倍赔偿</font></b>

4
00:02:29,590 --> 00:02:31,590
啊，你好啊，奈夫先生
Why, hello there, Mr. Neff.

5
00:02:43,880 --> 00:02:45,960
工作到很晚啊，奈夫先生？
Working pretty late, aren't you, Mr. Neff? 

6
00:02:45,960 --> 00:02:48,040
是很晚,上去吧
Late enough. Let's ride.

7
00:02:51,350 --> 00:02:54,280
-你看来面色很差     -我没事
You look kind of all in, at that. I'm fine.

8
00:02:54,720 --> 00:02:57,810
-保险生意如何，奈夫先生？   -很好
How is the insurance business, Mr. Neff? Okay.

9
00:02:58,690 --> 00:03:00,490
他们不肯卖我保险
They wouldn't ever sell me any.

10
00:03:00,560 --> 00:03:02,290
他们说我的心难以捉摸
They said I have something loose in my heart.

11
00:03:03,560 --> 00:03:05,860
-我心脏确实不好    -是吗? 
I say it's rheumatism. Yeah?

12
00:03:06,760 --> 00:03:07,990
12楼
Twelve.

13
00:05:03,750 --> 00:05:05,410
办公室备忘录
Office memorandum.

14
00:05:06,520 --> 00:05:09,420
沃特.奈夫致巴顿.基斯，索赔经理
Walter Neff to Barton Keyes, Claims Manager.

15
00:05:10,720 --> 00:05:12,920
洛杉矶，1938年7月16日
Los Angeles, July 16, 1938.

16
00:05:14,890 --> 00:05:16,360
亲爱的基斯
Dear Keyes...

17
00:05:17,960 --> 00:05:20,950
我猜你听到后会说这是招认
I suppose you'll call this a confession when you hear it.

18
00:05:21,030 --> 00:05:23,400
其实，我不喜欢  "招认"  这词
Well, I don't like the word confession.

19
00:05:23,470 --> 00:05:25,600
我只是想让你了解一些事情的真相
I just want to set you right about something you couldn't see...

20
00:05:25,670 --> 00:05:27,370
毕竟你正在为之头疼
because it was smack up against your nose.

21
00:05:28,540 --> 00:05:30,630
你以为自己是个一流索赔经理
You think you're such a hot potato as a Claims Manager...

22
00:05:30,710 --> 00:05:32,900
能一眼看穿虚假索赔
such a wolf on a phony claim.

23
00:05:34,010 --> 00:05:37,910
也许你确实是，但是看看迪崔克森的案子
Maybe you are, but let's take a look at that Dietrichson claim.

24
00:05:39,080 --> 00:05:41,310
意外和双倍赔偿
Accident and double indemnity.

25
00:05:42,190 --> 00:05:45,350
这事儿上你曾表现不错，基斯
You were pretty good in there for a while, Keyes.

26
00:05:45,620 --> 00:05:48,250
你说那不是意外。说对了。
You said it wasn't an accident. Check.

27
00:05:48,660 --> 00:05:51,090
你说那不是自杀。说对了。
You said it wasn't suicide. Check.

28
00:05:51,930 --> 00:05:55,090
你说那是谋杀。说对了。
You said it was murder. Check.

29
00:05:57,240 --> 00:05:59,760
你感觉十拿九稳了，是吗？ 
You thought you had it cold, didn't you?

30
00:05:59,840 --> 00:06:03,030
真相用包装纸包裹，附加粉红蝴蝶结
All wrapped up in tissue paper, with pink ribbons around it.

31
00:06:03,110 --> 00:06:04,630
堪称完美
It was perfect.

32
00:06:05,240 --> 00:06:08,240
但却不是，因为你犯了个错
Except it wasn't, because you made one mistake...

33
00:06:08,310 --> 00:06:10,210
只一个小小错误
just one little mistake.

34
00:06:11,450 --> 00:06:15,250
到确定凶手的那步，你搞错了人
When it came to picking the killer, you picked the wrong guy.

35
00:06:16,190 --> 00:06:18,920
你想知道是谁杀了迪崔克森？  
You want to know who killed Dietrichson?

36
00:06:19,560 --> 00:06:22,620
拿稳你的廉价雪茄，基斯
Hold tight to that cheap cigar of yours, Keyes.

37
00:06:24,060 --> 00:06:25,620
我杀了迪崔克森
I killed Dietrichson.

38
00:06:25,700 --> 00:06:28,560
我，沃特.奈夫，保险推销员
Me, Walter Neff, insurance salesman.

39
00:06:28,830 --> 00:06:31,770
35岁，未婚，没有前科
35 years old, unmarried, no visible scars...

40
00:06:33,940 --> 00:06:36,030
直至不久之前，我是说
until a while ago, that is.

41
00:06:37,510 --> 00:06:39,170
对，我杀了他
Yes, I killed him.

42
00:06:40,880 --> 00:06:42,900
我杀他是为了钱...
I killed him for money...

43
00:06:42,980 --> 00:06:44,570
和一个女人
and for a woman.

44
00:06:46,380 --> 00:06:50,550
而我没得到钱，而我没得到那女人
And I didn't get the money and I didn't get the woman.

45
00:06:52,760 --> 00:06:54,380
很有趣，是吧？
Pretty, isn't it?

46
00:07:08,240 --> 00:07:10,100
一切始于去年5月
It all began last May.

47
00:07:11,380 --> 00:07:12,570
那是5月底了
Around the end of May, it was.

48
00:07:14,750 --> 00:07:16,470
我去了格伦戴尔
I'd been out to Glendale 

49
00:07:16,470 --> 00:07:18,880
送一些乳业卡车的保单
to deliver a policy on some dairy trucks.

50
00:07:18,950 --> 00:07:20,050
回来路上  
On the way back 

51
00:07:20,050 --> 00:07:22,440
我记起洛斯菲利大道有宗汽车续保的事
I remembered this auto renewal near Los Feliz Boulevard.

52
00:07:22,550 --> 00:07:24,450
于是我开车过去
So I drove over there.

53
00:07:24,720 --> 00:07:26,490
那是一幢那种十来年前人们热衷的...
It was one of those California Spanish houses...

54
00:07:26,560 --> 00:07:29,460
加州-西班牙风格房子
everyone was nuts about 10 or 15 years ago.

55
00:07:30,030 --> 00:07:32,960
这一幢一定让某人花了3万块
This one must've cost somebody about $30,000.

56
00:07:33,230 --> 00:07:35,500
那是说，他已经付款完毕的话
That is, if he ever finished paying for it.

57
00:07:38,400 --> 00:07:39,870
迪崔克森先生在吗？
Is Mr. Dietrichson in?

58
00:07:39,940 --> 00:07:42,460
-谁要找他？    -我叫奈夫，沃特.奈夫
Who wants to see him? My name is Neff. Walter Neff.

59
00:07:42,540 --> 00:07:44,150
如果你想推销...  
If you're selling something... 

60
00:07:44,150 --> 00:07:45,770
你看，我是想跟迪崔克森先生谈...
Look, it's Mr. Dietrichson I want to talk to...

61
00:07:45,840 --> 00:07:47,000
不是来收杂志费的
and it's not magazine subscriptions.

62
00:07:47,080 --> 00:07:49,480
-听着，迪崔克森先生不在家     -他多久回来？  
Listen, Mr. Dietrichson is not in. How soon do you expect him?

63
00:07:49,550 --> 00:07:51,740
他回来时就回来了，这么说有用吗？
He'll be home when he gets here, if that's any help to you.

64
00:07:51,820 --> 00:07:53,550
什么事，妮蒂？是谁？ 
What is it, Nettie? Who is it?

65
00:07:53,620 --> 00:07:55,420
有人来找迪崔克森先生
It's for Mr. Dietrichson.

66
00:07:55,490 --> 00:07:57,580
我是迪崔克森太太，什么事？ 
I'm Mrs. Dietrichson. What is it?

67
00:07:58,260 --> 00:07:59,720
你好，迪崔克森太太
How do you do, Mrs. Dietrichson?

68
00:07:59,790 --> 00:08:01,720
我是沃特.奈夫，太平洋保险的
I'm Walter Neff, Pacific All Risk.

69
00:08:01,790 --> 00:08:04,960
-太平洋什么？   -太平洋保险公司
Pacific all what? The Pacific All Risk Insurance Company.

70
00:08:05,030 --> 00:08:07,020
是汽车保险续保的事
It's about some renewals on the automobiles.

71
00:08:07,100 --> 00:08:08,080
过去两星期里...
I've been trying to contact your husband 

72
00:08:08,080 --> 00:08:09,660
我一直想联系你先生
for the past two weeks...

73
00:08:09,730 --> 00:08:12,900
-但他从不在办公室    -我能做些什么？ 
but he's never in his office. Is there anything I can do?

74
00:08:12,970 --> 00:08:14,460
保险15号到期
The insurance ran out on the 15th.

75
00:08:14,540 --> 00:08:16,670
我不愿去想象...
I'd hate to think of your having a smashed fender...

76
00:08:16,740 --> 00:08:18,370
您出什么状况却无任何保险...
or something while you're not...

77
00:08:18,440 --> 00:08:19,700
这种情况
fully covered.

78
00:08:20,910 --> 00:08:23,180
也许我明白您的意思，奈夫先生
Perhaps I know what you mean, Mr. Neff.

79
00:08:23,250 --> 00:08:27,080
-我正在晒日光浴   -希望附近没鸽子
I've just been taking a sunbath. No pigeons around, I hope.

80
00:08:28,090 --> 00:08:29,420
关于那些保单， 
About those policies, 

81
00:08:29,420 --> 00:08:31,210
迪崔克森太太，抱歉打扰您，但是...
Mrs. Dietrichson, I hate to take up your time, but...

82
00:08:31,290 --> 00:08:32,620
没关系
Oh, that's all right.

83
00:08:32,690 --> 00:08:35,180
如果您能稍等我更衣，我马上下来
If you'll wait till I put something on, I'll be right down.

84
00:08:35,260 --> 00:08:38,160
妮蒂，带奈夫先生到客厅
Nettie, show Mr. Neff into the living room.

85
00:08:40,830 --> 00:08:42,160
客厅会在哪儿？  
Where would the living room be?

86
00:08:42,230 --> 00:08:44,670
那里，但他们把酒锁起来了
In there, but they keep the liquor locked up.

87
00:08:44,740 --> 00:08:47,730
没关系，我一向自有办法
It's all right. I always carry my own keys.

88
00:08:55,110 --> 00:08:56,770
客厅依然充斥着...
The living room was still stuffy...

89
00:08:56,850 --> 00:08:58,510
昨晚的雪茄气味
from last night's cigars.

90
00:08:59,380 --> 00:09:00,540
窗户紧闭...
The windows were closed...

91
00:09:00,620 --> 00:09:02,640
阳光从百叶窗透射进来...
and the sunshine coming in through the venetian blinds...

92
00:09:02,720 --> 00:09:04,950
让空气中的尘埃显现
showed up the dust in the air.

93
00:09:06,290 --> 00:09:08,020
钢琴上，几个精致相框里，  
On the piano, in a couple of fancy frames, 

94
00:09:08,020 --> 00:09:09,920
是迪崔克森先生和萝拉...
were Mr. Dietrichson and Lola...

95
00:09:09,990 --> 00:09:12,220
他和第一位妻子的女儿
his daughter by his first wife.

96
00:09:13,500 --> 00:09:15,730
他们有一缸那种小红金鱼...
They had a bowl of those little red goldfish...

97
00:09:15,800 --> 00:09:18,200
放在大沙发后面的桌子上
on the table behind the big davenport.

98
00:09:18,400 --> 00:09:19,630
但说实话，基斯
But to tell you the truth, Keyes...

99
00:09:19,700 --> 00:09:22,730
我当时对金鱼毫无兴趣
I wasn't a whole lot interested in goldfish right then.

100
00:09:22,810 --> 00:09:26,770
对汽车续保、迪崔克森先生和他女儿萝拉也是
Or in auto renewals, or in Mr. Dietrichson and his daughter Lola.

101
00:09:26,840 --> 00:09:29,070
我一心想着楼上那女的
I was thinking about that dame upstairs, 

102
00:09:29,070 --> 00:09:30,750
以及之前她看我的方式
and the way she had looked at me...

103
00:09:30,820 --> 00:09:33,510
我想再见到她，近一些...
and I wanted to see her again, close...

104
00:09:33,580 --> 00:09:36,310
而不是隔着那蠢楼梯
without that silly staircase between us.

105
00:09:41,560 --> 00:09:44,030
-没让您久等吧？   -一点没有，迪崔克森太太
I wasn't long, was I? Not at all, Mrs. Dietrichson.

106
00:09:44,100 --> 00:09:47,590
-希望我脸色还好    -很完美，在我看来
Hope I've got my face on straight. It's perfect, for my money.

107
00:09:47,670 --> 00:09:49,100
-你叫奈夫是吧？   -对  
Neff is the name, isn't it? Yeah.

108
00:09:49,170 --> 00:09:51,460
两个F，像费城那样，如果你知道那故事...
With two "F's," like in Philadelphia, if you know the story.

109
00:09:51,540 --> 00:09:54,100
-什么故事？     -费城故事啊
What story? The Philadelphia Story.

110
00:09:54,340 --> 00:09:56,330
不如坐下，你谈谈保险的事
Suppose we sit down and you tell me about the insurance.

111
00:09:56,410 --> 00:09:58,900
我丈夫什么也不告诉我
My husband never tells me anything.

112
00:09:58,980 --> 00:10:02,340
是关于你们的两部车，那凯迪拉克和克莱斯勒
Well, it's on your two cars, the LaSalle and the Plymouth.

113
00:10:03,810 --> 00:10:06,310
我们为迪崔克森先生负责这单保险...
We've been handling this insurance for Mr. Dietrichson 

114
00:10:06,310 --> 00:10:06,810
已三年了
for three years...

115
00:10:06,880 --> 00:10:09,410
我们不希望出现断供情况
and we'd hate to see the policies lapse.

116
00:10:09,820 --> 00:10:13,620
你的脚链很别致啊，迪崔克森太太
That's a honey of an anklet you're wearing, Mrs. Dietrichson.

117
00:10:13,820 --> 00:10:16,350
我刚说过，我们不希望保单断供
As I was saying, we'd hate to see the policies lapse.

118
00:10:16,430 --> 00:10:17,290
当然 ， 
Of course, 

119
00:10:17,290 --> 00:10:19,230
我们有三十天宽限期，最多了
we give them 30 days. That's all we're allowed to give.

120
00:10:19,300 --> 00:10:21,790
我猜他是在长滩的油田那边太忙了
I guess he's been too busy down at Long Beach in the oil fields.

121
00:10:21,870 --> 00:10:24,060
我能哪天晚上和他谈几分钟吗？ 
Couldn't I catch him at home some evening for a few minutes?

122
00:10:24,140 --> 00:10:26,070
应该可以， 但他8点前很少回家
I suppose so. But he's never home much before 8:00.

123
00:10:26,140 --> 00:10:27,470
我倒没问题
That's fine with me.

124
00:10:27,540 --> 00:10:29,560
你和汽车俱乐部没关系吧？  
You're not connected with the Automobile Club, are you?

125
00:10:29,640 --> 00:10:32,040
没，我是太平洋保险，怎么了？
No, the All Risk, Mrs. Dietrichson. Why?

126
00:10:32,110 --> 00:10:35,080
有个汽车俱乐部的人一直在找他
Somebody from the Automobile Club has been trying to get him.

127
00:10:35,150 --> 00:10:37,980
-他们的性价比更好吗？   -如果你丈夫是会员的话
Do they have a better rate? If your husband's a member.

128
00:10:38,050 --> 00:10:39,110
他不是
No, he isn't.

129
00:10:39,180 --> 00:10:41,020
那，他得先加入会员
Well, then he'd have to join the club 

130
00:10:41,030 --> 00:10:42,350
先交会员费
and pay the membership fee to start with.

131
00:10:42,420 --> 00:10:45,120
我从不抢人买卖，迪崔克森太太
I never knock the other fellow's merchandise, Mrs. Dietrichson.

132
00:10:45,190 --> 00:10:47,280
汽车俱乐部服务很好  
The Automobile Club's fine. 

133
00:10:47,280 --> 00:10:49,150
但我的服务也很好
I can do just as well for you, though.

134
00:10:49,230 --> 00:10:51,420
我这份保单很有吸引力
I have a very attractive policy here.

135
00:10:51,500 --> 00:10:52,640
两分钟都用不了...
It wouldn't take me two minutes 

136
00:10:52,640 --> 00:10:54,160
就能向您丈夫解释明白
to put it in front of your husband.

137
00:10:54,230 --> 00:10:56,790
举个例子，我们有个新规，撞车赔偿...
For instance, we're writing a new kind of 50% retention feature...

138
00:10:56,870 --> 00:10:58,890
有50％保留额度
in the collision coverage.

139
00:10:59,440 --> 00:11:01,870
你是个聪明的保险员，是吗？
You're a smart insurance man, aren't you, Mr. Neff?

140
00:11:01,940 --> 00:11:04,500
-我已经入行11年     -干的不错？ 
Well, I've been at it 11 years. Doing pretty well?

141
00:11:04,580 --> 00:11:05,940
够谋生了
It's a living.

142
00:11:06,680 --> 00:11:10,240
你只做汽车保险还是全部都做？ 
You handle just automobile insurance, or all kinds?

143
00:11:10,310 --> 00:11:12,420
全部。火灾险，地震险，盗窃险， 
All kinds. Fire, earthquake, theft, 

144
00:11:12,420 --> 00:11:13,750
公共债务，集体保险...
public liability, group insurance...

145
00:11:13,820 --> 00:11:16,250
工业事故等等，无所不包
industrial stuff and so on, right down the line.

146
00:11:16,390 --> 00:11:17,650
意外保险？ 
Accident insurance?

147
00:11:17,720 --> 00:11:19,950
意外保险？当然了，迪崔克森太太
Accident insurance? Sure, Mrs. Dietrichson.

148
00:11:21,890 --> 00:11:25,090
希望您告诉我那脚链上刻的什么？
Wish you'd tell me what's engraved on that anklet.

149
00:11:25,530 --> 00:11:28,050
-只是我的名字    -未请教？
Just my name. As, for instance?

150
00:11:29,630 --> 00:11:31,360
-菲莉丝    -菲莉丝啊？ 
Phyllis. Phyllis, huh?

151
00:11:32,040 --> 00:11:34,830
-我想我很喜欢  -但你不确定？
I think I like that. But you're not sure?

152
00:11:34,910 --> 00:11:38,070
我得开上几圈才知道
I'd have to drive it around the block a couple of times.

153
00:11:38,140 --> 00:11:40,870
奈夫先生，不如你明天晚上八点半左右来
Mr. Neff, why don't you drop by tomorrow evening around 8:30?

154
00:11:40,950 --> 00:11:42,810
-他会在家    -谁？
He'll be in then. Who?

155
00:11:42,880 --> 00:11:46,110
我丈夫啊，你不是着急想跟他谈吗？ 
My husband. You were anxious to talk to him, weren't you?

156
00:11:46,180 --> 00:11:49,080
是，曾经是，但我又觉得那不重要了...
Yeah, I was, but I'm sort of getting over the idea...

157
