Please don't talk like that. But that's the idea.

320
00:18:56,850 --> 00:18:59,840
有一次一根管子击中了工头
The other day a casing line snapped and caught the foreman.

321
00:18:59,920 --> 00:19:02,720
-他脊椎骨折住院了    -真糟糕
He's in the hospital with a broken back. That's bad.

322
00:19:02,790 --> 00:19:05,280
我想起来就觉得不安
It's got me jittery just thinking about it.

323
00:19:05,360 --> 00:19:07,590
如果我丈夫也遇上这种事呢
Suppose something like that happened to my husband.

324
00:19:07,660 --> 00:19:09,350
有可能
It could. Well...

325
00:19:10,730 --> 00:19:14,030
-你不认为他应该买意外险吗？   -嗯
don't you think he ought to have accident insurance? Mmm-hmm.

326
00:19:15,070 --> 00:19:17,400
他买哪种险合适？  
What kind of insurance could he have?

327
00:19:17,470 --> 00:19:19,700
足够支付医疗费用的都行
Enough to cover doctors and hospital bills.

328
00:19:19,770 --> 00:19:21,830
例如每周125现金保障
Say $125 a week cash benefit.

329
00:19:21,910 --> 00:19:24,310
最高赔偿达5万元
And he'd rate around $50,000 capital sum.

330
00:19:24,370 --> 00:19:27,640
-最高赔偿？什么意思？     -如果他死了  
Capital sum? What's that? In case he gets killed.

331
00:19:28,450 --> 00:19:30,850
也许我不该这么说
Maybe I shouldn't have said that.

332
00:19:30,910 --> 00:19:33,280
我猜你做这一行要想得面面俱到
I suppose you have to think of everything in your business.

333
00:19:33,350 --> 00:19:34,750
你丈夫会理解的
Well, your husband would understand.

334
00:19:34,820 --> 00:19:36,600
我觉得我可以让他考虑...
I'm sure I could sell him on the idea of 

335
00:19:36,600 --> 00:19:37,620
购买意外险
some accident protection.

336
00:19:37,690 --> 00:19:39,250
不如我跟他谈谈？ 
Why don't I talk to him about it?

337
00:19:39,320 --> 00:19:41,480
你可以试试，但他很固执
You could try, but he's pretty tough-going.

338
00:19:41,560 --> 00:19:43,650
人们起初都很固执
They're all tough at first.

339
00:19:44,460 --> 00:19:45,690
他头脑很复杂
He has a lot on his mind.

340
00:19:45,760 --> 00:19:47,490
他不懂什么是倾听...
He doesn't seem to want to listen to anything...

341
00:19:47,560 --> 00:19:50,400
除了收音机里的棒球赛
except maybe a baseball game on the radio.

342
00:19:50,730 --> 00:19:52,850
有时候我们坐个整晚
Sometimes we sit here all evening 

343
00:19:52,850 --> 00:19:54,670
相互之间却不吐一字
and never say a word to each other.

344
00:19:54,770 --> 00:19:58,400
-听起来挺沉闷      -我只是坐这织毛衣
Sounds pretty dull. So, I just sit and knit.

345
00:19:59,780 --> 00:20:01,110
你嫁他是为了这个吗？  
Is that what you married him for?

346
00:20:01,180 --> 00:20:04,340
也许我喜欢他手持毛线的样子
Maybe I like the way his thumbs hold up the wool.

347
00:20:04,820 --> 00:20:07,080
如果他的手累了...
Anytime his thumbs get tired...

348
00:20:07,150 --> 00:20:09,520
有我在，你不用织什么毛衣
Only, with me around, you wouldn't have to knit.

349
00:20:09,590 --> 00:20:11,680
-不用吗？     -你尽管放心，不用
Wouldn't I? You bet your life, you wouldn't.

350
00:20:14,760 --> 00:20:18,190
加点朗姆酒也许更好一点
Wonder if a little rum would get this up on its feet.

351
00:20:20,260 --> 00:20:22,790
我想问你件事，沃特
I want to ask you something, Walter.

352
00:20:25,040 --> 00:20:26,830
我能够不去打扰他...
Could I get an accident policy for him 

353
00:20:26,830 --> 00:20:28,630
而给他买份意外险吗？
without bothering him at all?

354
00:20:28,710 --> 00:20:29,730
再说一次？
How's that, again?

355
00:20:29,810 --> 00:20:31,500
这对你也更容易了 
It would make it easier for you, too. 

356
00:20:31,500 --> 00:20:32,780
你都不用和他谈了
You wouldn't even have to talk to him.

357
00:20:32,840 --> 00:20:34,370
我有点私房钱
I have a little allowance of my own.

358
00:20:34,440 --> 00:20:37,640
我可以付款，他不用知道这事
I could pay for it and he needn't know anything about it.

359
00:20:40,080 --> 00:20:41,280
为什么他不用知道？  
Why shouldn't he know?

360
00:20:41,350 --> 00:20:43,750
因为他不想要意外险
Because he doesn't want accident insurance.

361
00:20:43,820 --> 00:20:45,290
他对此有点迷信 
He's superstitious about it. 

362
00:20:45,290 --> 00:20:47,760
很多人都是。真有趣，对吗？
A lot of people are. That's funny, isn't it?

363
00:20:47,820 --> 00:20:49,740
如果能那样办的话
If there was a way to get it like that, 

364
00:20:49,740 --> 00:20:51,990
能省掉不少麻烦
all the worry would be over.

365
00:20:52,930 --> 00:20:56,020
-懂我意思吗，沃特？    -当然，我眼睛雪亮
See what I mean, Walter? Sure. I got good eyesight.

366
00:20:56,100 --> 00:20:58,830
你是说，你希望他在不知情的情况下拥有保险
You mean you want him to have the policy without him knowing it.

367
00:20:58,900 --> 00:21:00,920
那意味着，他不知情这事...
And that means without the insurance company knowing 

368
00:21:00,920 --> 00:21:01,930
保险公司那边也不能知道
that he doesn't know it.

369
00:21:02,010 --> 00:21:04,800
-是这么设想的吧？   -有什么问题吗？ 
That's the setup, isn't it? Is there anything wrong with it?

370
00:21:04,880 --> 00:21:06,210
没有，我看很好
No, I think it's lovely.

371
00:21:06,280 --> 00:21:07,410
然后，如果某个雨夜，
Then, if some dark, wet night, 

372
00:21:07,410 --> 00:21:08,710
那钻油塔确实砸向他...
that crown block did fall on him...

373
00:21:08,780 --> 00:21:09,840
什么钻油塔？  
What crown block?

374
00:21:09,910 --> 00:21:11,820
但有时钻油塔自己办不到  
Only sometimes it can't quite make it on its own, 

375
00:21:11,830 --> 00:21:13,010
它得需要一点帮助
it has to have a little help.

376
00:21:13,080 --> 00:21:14,410
我不知道你在说什么
I don't know what you're talking about.

377
00:21:14,480 --> 00:21:15,920
当然，不一定非是钻油塔
Of course, it doesn't have to be a crown block.

378
00:21:15,990 --> 00:21:18,050
也可能是汽车撞了他
It can be a car backing over him, 

379
00:21:18,050 --> 00:21:19,080
也可能从楼上窗口坠楼
or he could fall out of the upstairs window.

380
00:21:19,160 --> 00:21:21,250
诸如此类，下面就是太平间接手了
Any little thing like that, just so it's a morgue job.

381
00:21:21,330 --> 00:21:23,560
-你疯了？    -没那么疯
Are you crazy? Not that crazy.

382
00:21:25,630 --> 00:21:27,360
-再见，迪崔克森太太    -怎么了？  
Goodbye, Mrs. Dietrichson. What's the matter?

383
00:21:29,700 --> 00:21:32,330
听着宝贝，你没法全身而退
Look, baby, you can't get away with it.

384
00:21:34,200 --> 00:21:35,800
你想干掉他，不是吗？
You want to knock him off, don't you?

385
00:21:35,870 --> 00:21:37,340
你太含血喷人了
That's a horrible thing to say.

386
00:21:37,410 --> 00:21:38,700
你以为我是什么人? 
What'd you think I was, anyway?

387
00:21:38,780 --> 00:21:40,350
直接走进...
A guy that walks into 

388
00:21:40,350 --> 00:21:41,140
一个漂亮少妇家的客厅然后说：
a good looking dame's front parlor and says:

389
00:21:41,210 --> 00:21:43,180
“下午好，我给做丈夫的卖意外险”
"Good afternoon, I sell accident insurance on husbands.

390
00:21:43,250 --> 00:21:44,510
“您对您丈夫厌烦了吗？” 
"You got one that's been around too long?

391
00:21:44,580 --> 00:21:46,240
“是不是想将他变成钱？”
"One you'd like to turn into a little hard cash?

392
00:21:46,320 --> 00:21:48,220
“对我笑一个 ，我就帮你搞定”
"Just give me a smile and I'll help you collect. "

393
00:21:48,290 --> 00:21:51,950
-你认为我是蠢蛋啊    -我认为你是坏蛋
Boy, what a dope you must think I am. I think you're rotten.

394
00:21:52,020 --> 00:21:54,220
我认为你很棒，只要我不是你丈夫
I think you're swell, so long as I'm not your husband.

395
00:21:54,290 --> 00:21:57,230
-给我滚    -不用你说
Get out of here. You bet I'll get out of here, baby.

396
00:21:57,290 --> 00:21:59,490
我会走的，尽快
I'll get out of here, but quick.

397
00:22:09,470 --> 00:22:11,910
我态度坚决，直截了当
So I let her have it straight between the eyes.

398
00:22:11,980 --> 00:22:14,500
我没上当，这次没有
She didn't fool me for a minute, not this time.

399
00:22:14,750 --> 00:22:16,210
我知道这是个烫手山芋
I knew I had hold of a red-hot poker...

400
00:22:16,280 --> 00:22:19,010
必须在烫烂我的手之前扔掉
and the time to drop it was before it burned my hand off.

401
00:22:19,750 --> 00:22:22,020
我停在汽车餐厅，要了瓶啤酒
I stopped at a drive-in for a bottle of beer, 

402
00:22:22,020 --> 00:22:23,650
这半天一直想喝的
the one I had wanted all along...

403
00:22:23,720 --> 00:22:25,120
现在更想了
only I wanted it worse now, 

404
00:22:25,120 --> 00:22:27,590
来除掉她那冰茶的味道
to get rid of the sour taste of her iced tea...

405
00:22:27,660 --> 00:22:29,560
以及和它有关的一切
and everything that went with it.

406
00:22:29,660 --> 00:22:31,010
我不想回办公室
I didn't want to go back to the office 

407
00:22:31,010 --> 00:22:32,820
就去了三街和西街...
so I dropped by a bowling alley...

408
00:22:32,900 --> 00:22:35,420
的保龄球馆，打了几局...
at Third and Western and rolled a few lines...

409
00:22:35,500 --> 00:22:38,590
使自己分散注意力
to get my mind thinking about something else for a while.

410
00:22:39,440 --> 00:22:40,700
走时我没胃口吃饭
I didn't feel like eating dinner 

411
00:22:40,710 --> 00:22:43,670
也不想去什么娱乐
when I left, and I didn't feel like a show.

412
00:22:43,740 --> 00:22:47,140
于是开车回家，停车，上楼
So, I drove home, put the car away and went up to my apartment.

413
00:22:48,980 --> 00:22:51,380
天开始下雨，我眼看天色渐黑
It had begun to rain outside and I watched it get dark...

414
00:22:51,450 --> 00:22:53,510
却连灯都没开
and didn't even turn on the light.

415
00:22:53,920 --> 00:22:55,380
那也对我毫无帮助
That didn't help me either.

416
00:22:55,950 --> 00:22:57,280
我心乱如麻
I was all twisted up inside...

417
00:22:57,350 --> 00:23:00,190
烫手山芋还在我手里捧着
and I was still holding on to that red-hot poker.

418
00:23:00,560 --> 00:23:02,000
当时我才意识到
And right then it came over me 

419
00:23:02,000 --> 00:23:04,320
我还一点都没走出来
that I hadn't walked out on anything at all.

420
00:23:04,530 --> 00:23:06,860
那诱惑太过强烈...
That the hook was too strong...

421
00:23:06,930 --> 00:23:09,490
我和她之间还没有结束
that this wasn't the end between her and me.

422
00:23:09,630 --> 00:23:11,230
反而才刚刚开始
It was only the beginning.

423
00:23:12,400 --> 00:23:14,470
所以，8点门铃响起...  
So at 8:00 the bell would ring 

424
00:23:14,470 --> 00:23:16,740
我不假思索就知道来人是谁
and I'd know who it was without even having to think.

425
00:23:17,070 --> 00:23:19,740
好像这是最自然不过的事
As if it was the most natural thing in the world.

426
00:23:23,480 --> 00:23:26,450
嗨，你今天下午忘拿帽子
Hello. You forgot your hat this afternoon.

427
00:23:27,250 --> 00:23:29,880
-是吗？     -不想让我拿进来吗？  
Did I? Don't you want me to bring it in?

428
00:23:30,590 --> 00:23:31,710
好
Sure.

429
00:23:33,520 --> 00:23:35,220
放椅子上
Put it on the chair.

430
00:23:43,930 --> 00:23:46,400
-你怎么知道我住址？    -电话薄
How'd you know where I live? It's in the phone book.

431
00:23:47,270 --> 00:23:49,000
-正在下雨    -对
It's raining. Yeah.

432
00:23:50,070 --> 00:23:51,940
脱下外衣坐下吧
Peel off your coat and sit down.

433
00:23:55,050 --> 00:23:56,100
你丈夫出去了？ 
Your husband out?

434
00:23:56,180 --> 00:23:58,170
对，长滩，要建一座新井
Yes. Long Beach. They're spudding in a new well.

435
00:23:58,250 --> 00:24:00,410
他说晚点回来，大约9点半
He phoned he'd be late. About 9:30.

436
00:24:01,590 --> 00:24:03,780
该说你很高兴见到我了吧？
It's about time you said you were glad to see me.

437
00:24:03,850 --> 00:24:05,290
我知道你不会那样就拉倒的
I knew you wouldn't leave it like that.

438
00:24:05,360 --> 00:24:08,350
-哪样？     -今天下午那样
Like what? Like it was this afternoon.

439
00:24:08,430 --> 00:24:10,070
我一定是说错话
I must have said something 

440
00:24:10,070 --> 00:24:11,720
让你严重误会了
that gave you a terribly wrong impression.

441
00:24:11,800 --> 00:24:14,700
你千万不能那么看我，沃特
You must never think anything like that about me, Walter.

442
00:24:14,760 --> 00:24:16,030
-好的     -不好
Okay. No, it's not okay.

443
00:24:16,100 --> 00:24:18,930
-如果你不信我就不好    -你想让我怎样？  
Not if you don't believe me. What do you want me to do?

444
00:24:19,940 --> 00:24:21,630
我想你对我好一些
I want you to be nice to me.

445
00:24:22,440 --> 00:24:24,930
像你第一次来我家那样
Like the first time you came to the house.

446
00:24:25,010 --> 00:24:27,240
回不去了
It can't be like the first time.

447
00:24:27,310 --> 00:24:30,110
-发生了一些事    -我知道
Something's happened. I know it has.

448
00:24:30,910 --> 00:24:32,680
在我们之间
It's happened to us.

449
00:24:35,220 --> 00:24:39,210
我觉得他在盯着我，但不是出于关心
I feel as if he was watching me. Not that he cares. Not anymore.

450
00:24:40,590 --> 00:24:43,530
他勒住我让我无法呼吸
He keeps me on a leash so tight I can't breathe.

451
00:24:43,590 --> 00:24:46,120
他不是在长滩吗？放松
He's in Long Beach, isn't he? Relax.

452
00:24:46,500 --> 00:24:48,520
也许我不该来
Maybe I oughtn't to have come.

453
00:24:48,600 --> 00:24:51,290
-也许不该     -你想我走？  
Maybe you oughtn't. You want me to go?

454
00:24:51,370 --> 00:24:53,670
-如果你想     -现在？  
If you want to. Right now?

455
00:24:53,740 --> 00:24:55,030
当然，现在...
Sure, right now.

456
00:25:11,320 --> 00:25:14,550
-我为你疯狂，宝贝     -我也为你疯狂，沃特
I'm crazy about you, baby. I'm crazy about you, Walter.

457
00:25:14,790 --> 00:25:17,350
你头发上的香水，叫什么名字？  
That perfume on your hair. What's the name of it?

458
00:25:17,790 --> 00:25:20,390
我不知道，我在昂塞纳达买的
I don't know. I bought it in Ensenada.

459
00:25:21,500 --> 00:25:23,660
你应该喝点那种玫瑰红葡萄酒来搭配
You ought to have some of that pink wine to go with it.

460
00:25:23,730 --> 00:25:26,630
起泡的那种，但我只有波本
The kind that bubbles. All I got is bourbon.

461
00:25:27,800 --> 00:25:29,670
波本也行啊，沃特
Bourbon is fine, Walter.

462
00:25:36,710 --> 00:25:38,580
拿两个杯子，好吗？
Get a couple of glasses, will you?

463
00:25:46,220 --> 00:25:48,160
-加苏打水？    -白水，谢谢
Club soda? Plain water, please.

464
00:25:49,830 --> 00:25:51,050
知道吗？ 六个月前...
You know, about six months ago 

465
00:25:51,050 --> 00:25:53,020
有人在浴缸里踩肥皂滑倒
a guy slipped on a cake of soap in his bathtub...

466
00:25:53,100 --> 00:25:55,430
摔晕了然后淹死了
and knocked himself cold and was drowned.

467
00:25:55,900 --> 00:25:57,870
而他买了意外险
Only he had accident insurance.

468
00:25:57,930 --> 00:26:00,460
他们验尸了，她就没跑掉
So they had an autopsy and she didn't get away with it.

469
00:26:00,540 --> 00:26:02,630
-谁没跑掉？    -他老婆
Who didn't? His wife.

470
00:26:04,740 --> 00:26:07,210
还有个男的被枪打死的保险案子
Then there was a case of a guy who was found shot.

471
00:26:07,310 --> 00:26:09,650
他老婆说他在擦枪  
His wife said he was cleaning a gun 

472
00:26:09,650 --> 00:26:10,510
不小心打中肚子
and his stomach got in the way.

473
00:26:11,210 --> 00:26:14,210
最后她得到3平米大的监狱单间
All she collected was a three-to-ten stretch in Tehachapi.

474
00:26:15,050 --> 00:26:17,080
也许她觉得值得
Perhaps it was worth it to her.

475
00:26:19,320 --> 00:26:21,920
看你能不能拿到客厅
See if you can carry that as far as the living room.

476
00:26:25,800 --> 00:26:28,890
这地方不错，谁替你收拾？ 
It's nice here, Walter. Who takes care of it for you?

477
00:26:28,970 --> 00:26:31,560
一个黑人妇女每周来打扫两次
A colored woman comes in a couple of times a week.

478
00:26:31,640 --> 00:26:34,700
-自己做早饭吗？    -有时榨点橙汁
Cook your own breakfast? Squeeze a grapefruit once in a while.

479
00:26:34,800 --> 00:26:37,710
-其余的在街角杂货店买    -听起来不错
Get the rest down at the corner drugstore. Sounds wonderful.

480
00:26:37,770 --> 00:26:39,500
周围仅有陌生人
Just strangers beside you.

481
00:26:39,940 --> 00:26:42,280
你不认识他们 就不会恨他们
You don't know them and you don't hate them.

482
00:26:42,450 --> 00:26:43,970
你不用早上坐在餐桌...
You don't have to sit across the table...

483
00:26:44,050 --> 00:26:46,600
向着他和他女儿微笑...
and smile at him and 

484
00:26:46,600 --> 00:26:47,240
日复一日的
that daughter of his every morning of your life.

485
00:26:47,320 --> 00:26:50,580
什么女儿？ 钢琴上的女孩？ 
What daughter? You mean the little girl on the piano?

486
00:26:50,950 --> 00:26:52,680
萝拉，她跟我们同住
Lola. She lives with us.

487
00:26:52,760 --> 00:26:55,280
他替她想的更多
He thinks a lot more of her than he does of me.

488
00:26:55,690 --> 00:26:58,090
