What's wrong with that? 

653
00:34:44,370 --> 00:34:46,350
我不能开心一下吗，哪怕一年才一次？
Can't I have a little fun, even once a year?

654
00:34:46,430 --> 00:34:48,090
斯坦福的足球很厉害
Great football school, Stanford.

655
00:34:48,160 --> 00:34:50,160
-你踢足球吗，迪崔克森先生？     -左卫
Did you play football, Mr. Dietrichson? Left guard.

656
00:34:50,230 --> 00:34:51,860
-几乎入选校队。签哪里？  
Almost made the varsity, too. Where do I sign?

657
00:34:51,930 --> 00:34:53,270
那条线
The bottom line.

658
00:34:57,910 --> 00:34:59,930
-两份都签      -签两次？
Both copies, please. Sign twice, huh?

659
00:35:00,010 --> 00:35:01,310
对，一份是业务员的
Yes. One is the agent's copy.

660
00:35:01,380 --> 00:35:05,340
-我自己要存档     -存档，两份，三份，真麻烦
I need it for my files. Files. Duplicates. Triplicates.

661
00:35:11,090 --> 00:35:12,550
谢谢，迪崔克森先生
Thank you, Mr. Dietrichson.

662
00:35:12,620 --> 00:35:13,830
别担心支票  
Don't worry about the check, 

663
00:35:13,830 --> 00:35:15,460
我改天去你办公室取
I can pick it up at your office some morning.

664
00:35:15,530 --> 00:35:17,760
-要多少钱?    -147.5元
How much you taking me for? $147.50.

665
00:35:17,830 --> 00:35:20,520
我觉得今晚说够了保险的事了，奈夫先生
I think that's enough insurance for one evening, Mr. Neff.

666
00:35:20,600 --> 00:35:21,790
足够了
Plenty.

667
00:35:25,700 --> 00:35:26,960
上来时给我带些苏打水  
Bring me some soda when you come up, 

668
00:35:26,960 --> 00:35:28,360
菲莉丝。  晚安，奈夫先生
Phyllis. Good night, Mr. Neff.

669
00:35:28,440 --> 00:35:29,460
晚安，迪崔克森先生
Good night, Mr. Dietrichson.

670
00:35:29,540 --> 00:35:32,130
你的帽子在走廊，奈夫先生
I think you left your hat in the hall, Mr. Neff.

671
00:35:47,660 --> 00:35:49,450
晚安，奈夫先生
Good night, Mr. Neff.

672
00:35:52,130 --> 00:35:53,320
-好了吗，沃特？   -好了
All right, Walter? Fine.

673
00:35:53,400 --> 00:35:55,300
-他签了，是不是？    -当然，你亲眼看见
He signed it, didn't he? Sure he signed it. You saw him.

674
00:35:55,360 --> 00:35:57,300
现在听着，去帕洛阿尔托的事，他何时出发？  
Now, listen. That trip to Palo Alto. When does he leave?

675
00:35:57,370 --> 00:35:58,360
月底
End of the month.

676
00:35:58,430 --> 00:35:59,420
-开车去？     -一向都是
He drives, huh? He always drives.

677
00:35:59,500 --> 00:36:01,130
这次不行，你要让他坐火车
Not this time. You're gonna make him take the train.

678
00:36:01,200 --> 00:36:02,760
-为什么？     -因为坐火车会更完美
Why? Because it's all worked out for a train.

679
00:36:02,840 --> 00:36:05,210
听着宝贝，每桩意外险都会有个条款...
Listen, baby. There's a clause in every accident policy...

680
00:36:05,270 --> 00:36:07,140
叫做双倍赔偿
a little thing called double indemnity.

681
00:36:07,210 --> 00:36:08,900
算是保险公司给顾客
The insurance companies put it in 

682
00:36:08,900 --> 00:36:10,110
的额外优惠
as a sort of come-on for the customers.

683
00:36:10,180 --> 00:36:12,340
意思是他们在特定事故时会付双倍
That means they pay double on certain accidents.

684
00:36:12,420 --> 00:36:14,040
那种几乎不会发生的事故
The kind that almost never happen.

685
00:36:14,120 --> 00:36:16,610
比如说，顾客在火车上死亡
Like for instance, if a guy is killed on the train...

686
00:36:16,690 --> 00:36:19,120
他们就会付10万而不是5万
they pay $100,000 instead of $50,000.

687
00:36:19,190 --> 00:36:21,620
-我明白了   -我们要做到极限
I see. We're hitting it for the limit, baby.

688
00:36:21,690 --> 00:36:24,220
所以必须是火车
That's why it's got to be the train.

689
00:36:25,530 --> 00:36:28,360
他会坐火车的，沃特，就像你需要的
It'll be the train, Walter. Just the way you want it.

690
00:36:28,430 --> 00:36:30,330
彻头彻尾
Straight down the line.

691
00:36:49,720 --> 00:36:51,310
嗨，奈夫先生
Hello, Mr. Neff.

692
00:36:52,720 --> 00:36:53,950
是我
It's me.

693
00:36:54,690 --> 00:36:57,060
-有什么事？    -我在等你
Is anything wrong? I've been waiting for you.

694
00:36:57,130 --> 00:36:58,220
等我？为什么？
For me? Why?

695
00:36:58,290 --> 00:37:01,590
我想让你捎我一段，如果顺路
I thought you could let me ride with you, if you're going my way.

696
00:37:06,740 --> 00:37:10,190
-你走哪条路？    -下山，去维蒙特
Which way would that be? Down the hill. Down Vermont.

697
00:37:10,270 --> 00:37:13,270
当然，维蒙特街与富兰克林街西北角，是吗？  
Sure. Vermont and Franklin. Northwest corner, wasn't it?

698
00:37:13,340 --> 00:37:14,670
没问题，迪崔克森小姐
Be glad to, Miss Dietrichson.

699
00:37:19,120 --> 00:37:21,080
去溜冰？  
Going roller-skating, huh?

700
00:37:21,220 --> 00:37:24,580
-你喜欢溜冰？   -溜不溜都行
You like roller-skating? I can take it or leave it.

701
00:37:25,760 --> 00:37:28,660
-但今晚不会溜？    -是的  
Only tonight you're leaving it? Yes, I am.

702
00:37:30,060 --> 00:37:32,690
我在家里很难熬
I'm having a very tough time at home.

703
00:37:32,760 --> 00:37:36,130
我爸不懂我，菲莉丝恨我
My father doesn't understand me and Phyllis hates me.

704
00:37:36,570 --> 00:37:40,090
-听起来真糟      -所以我得偶尔撒谎
Sounds tough, all right. That's why I have to lie sometimes.

705
00:37:40,170 --> 00:37:41,570
你是说不去维蒙特街与富兰克林街 ？ 
You mean it's not Vermont and Franklin?

706
00:37:41,640 --> 00:37:43,570
地点倒是真的
It's Vermont and Franklin all right.

707
00:37:43,640 --> 00:37:46,770
但不是安妮.马修斯，而是尼诺.扎切提
Only it's not Anne Matthews. It's Nino Zachetti.

708
00:37:47,940 --> 00:37:49,910
你不会告发我，对吧？  
You won't tell on me, will you?

709
00:37:49,980 --> 00:37:52,710
-我要考虑一下     -尼诺不是我爸说的那么差
I'd have to think it over. Nino's not what my father says at all.

710
00:37:52,780 --> 00:37:55,880
他只是运气差，他在南加州大学读医科
He's just had bad luck. He was doing premed at USC...

711
00:37:55,950 --> 00:37:58,920
晚上在剧院做引座员
and working nights as an usher in a theater downtown.

712
00:37:58,990 --> 00:38:01,650
因为学分不足而被退学
Got behind in his credits, flunked out.

713
00:38:01,790 --> 00:38:05,750
然后与上司顶嘴被解雇，他太鲁莽
Then he lost his job for talking back. He's so hot-headed.

714
00:38:06,960 --> 00:38:08,260
代价真大，不是吗？
Becomes expensive, doesn't it?

715
00:38:08,330 --> 00:38:10,820
我爸大概认为没人配得上他女儿
Guess my father thinks nobody's good enough for his daughter...

716
00:38:10,900 --> 00:38:13,130
除了标准石油公司老板
except maybe the guy that owns Standard Oil.

717
00:38:13,200 --> 00:38:16,970
我希望他理解我，我不能放弃尼诺
I wish he'd see it my way. I can't give Nino up.

718
00:38:18,370 --> 00:38:20,570
船到桥头自然直，迪崔克森小姐
It'll all straighten out, Miss Dietrichson.

719
00:38:20,640 --> 00:38:22,300
我想会吧  
I suppose it will sometime. 

720
00:38:22,300 --> 00:38:24,810
就是这里，奈夫先生
This is the corner right here, Mr. Neff.

721
00:38:27,250 --> 00:38:30,010
尼诺？过来，尼诺
Nino? Over here, Nino.

722
00:38:38,690 --> 00:38:41,250
-这是奈夫先生，尼诺...     -你好，尼诺
This is Mr. Neff, Nino. Hello, Nino.

723
00:38:41,500 --> 00:38:42,960
我大名扎切提
The name is Zachetti.

724
00:38:43,030 --> 00:38:45,690
尼诺，别这样，奈夫先生送我来的
Nino, please. Mr. Neff gave me a ride from the house.

725
00:38:45,770 --> 00:38:46,860
我告诉了他我们的事
I told him all about us.

726
00:38:46,940 --> 00:38:48,300
何必要告诉他？  
Why does he have to get told about us?

727
00:38:48,370 --> 00:38:50,360
不用担心奈夫先生
We don't have to worry about Mr. Neff, Nino.

728
00:38:50,440 --> 00:38:52,000
我不是担心
I'm not doing any worrying.

729
00:38:52,070 --> 00:38:53,370
只是别四处张扬
Just don't you broadcast so much.

730
00:38:53,440 --> 00:38:55,170
你怎么回事，尼诺？ 
Well, what's the matter with you, Nino?

731
00:38:55,240 --> 00:38:57,740
-他是朋友     -我没有朋友
Why, he's a friend. I don't have any friends.

732
00:38:57,810 --> 00:39:00,080
就算有，我喜欢自己选择
If I did, I like to pick them myself. Come on.

733
00:39:00,150 --> 00:39:02,480
听着，她要搭车，我就捎她一段而已 
Look, sonny, she needed a ride, so I brought her along.

734
00:39:02,550 --> 00:39:04,710
有什么不好吗？  
Is that anything to get tough about?

735
00:39:04,790 --> 00:39:07,260
好了，萝拉，决定吧，你来不来？  
All right, Lola, make up your mind. Are you coming or aren't you?

736
00:39:07,320 --> 00:39:09,120
当然来
Of course I'm coming.

737
00:39:11,660 --> 00:39:14,960
别介意他，奈夫先生，谢谢载我一程
Don't mind him, Mr. Neff. And thanks a lot for the ride.

738
00:39:15,030 --> 00:39:17,360
你真好。  尼诺？  
You're awfully sweet. Nino?

739
00:39:22,670 --> 00:39:24,470
她是个好女孩
She was a nice kid.

740
00:39:24,740 --> 00:39:27,710
他可能也比表面上好一些
Maybe he was a little better than he sounded.

741
00:39:27,780 --> 00:39:30,060
但当时
But right then 

742
00:39:30,060 --> 00:39:31,210
想起我身后的公文包...
it gave me a nasty feeling to be thinking about them at all...

743
00:39:31,280 --> 00:39:33,130
和里面她父亲的签名...
with that briefcase right behind my head 

744
00:39:33,130 --> 00:39:34,980
以及签名的含义时
that had her father's signature in it...

745
00:39:35,050 --> 00:39:37,180
我浑身不自在
and what that signature meant.

746
00:39:37,250 --> 00:39:39,480
签名的含义是他离死不远了
It meant he was a dead pigeon.

747
00:39:39,720 --> 00:39:43,620
那只是时间问题，而且时间不长了
It was only a question of time, and not very much time at that.

748
00:39:43,690 --> 00:39:46,420
知道洛斯菲利兹的大市场吗，基斯？  
You know that big market up on Los Feliz, Keyes?

749
00:39:47,200 --> 00:39:50,720
那是菲莉丝和我挑选的碰头处
That's the place Phyllis and I had picked for a meeting place.

750
00:39:50,800 --> 00:39:52,890
我脑中计划已经成型
I already had most of the plan in my head...

751
00:39:52,970 --> 00:39:55,270
但好多细节仍需理清
but a lot of details had to be worked out.

752
00:39:55,340 --> 00:39:58,900
而日子到时她必须了然于心
And she had to know them all by heart when the time came.

753
00:39:59,310 --> 00:40:01,940
从今我们必须小心翼翼
We had to be very careful from now on.

754
00:40:02,080 --> 00:40:04,710
不能让人看见我们一起
We couldn't let anybody see us together.

755
00:40:04,780 --> 00:40:07,680
连通电话也不行
We couldn't even talk to each other on the telephone.

756
00:40:07,750 --> 00:40:10,620
至少不能用双方座机
Not from her house or at my office, anyway.

757
00:40:11,350 --> 00:40:13,790
所以她每天上午11点去市场
So she was to be in the market every morning about 11:00, 

758
00:40:13,790 --> 00:40:15,620
买些东西
buying stuff.

759
00:40:15,860 --> 00:40:19,290
而我需要时可以在那里碰到她
And I could sort of run into her there any day I wanted to.

760
00:40:19,360 --> 00:40:21,690
装作偶然
Sort of accidentally on purpose.

761
00:40:22,570 --> 00:40:25,060
-沃特，我想...      -别那么大声
Walter, I wanted to... Not so loud.

762
00:40:26,500 --> 00:40:28,200
我从昨天起就想和你谈谈
I wanted to talk to you, ever since yesterday.

763
00:40:28,270 --> 00:40:30,400
-让我先说，事情已搞定
Let me talk first. It's all set.

764
00:40:30,470 --> 00:40:32,960
意外险批下来了，保单在我口袋里
The accident policy came through. I've got it in my pocket.

765
00:40:33,040 --> 00:40:35,980
支票我也拿到，我在油田见过他
I got his check, too. I saw him down in the oil fields.

766
00:40:36,050 --> 00:40:38,170
他以为支付的是汽车保险
He thought he was paying for the auto insurance.

767
00:40:38,250 --> 00:40:39,390
支票抬头只写了保险公司
The check's just made out to the company, 

768
00:40:39,390 --> 00:40:41,110
所以支付什么都行
so it could be for anything.

769
00:40:41,180 --> 00:40:43,980
但你得寄出一张汽车保险支票，明白吗？
But you have to send a check for the auto insurance, see?

770
00:40:44,050 --> 00:40:45,310
那就没问题了  
It'll be all right that way, 

771
00:40:45,310 --> 00:40:47,110
因为其中一辆车在你的名下
because one of the cars is in your name.

772
00:40:47,190 --> 00:40:48,950
打开包，快点
Open your bag. Quick.

773
00:40:54,130 --> 00:40:55,530
你能打开保险箱吗？  
Can you get in the safe-deposit box?

774
00:40:55,600 --> 00:40:57,590
-能，我俩都有钥匙     -好
Yes. We both have keys. Fine.

775
00:40:57,670 --> 00:40:59,960
但先别放保单进去，我再告诉你时间
But don't put the policy in there yet. I'll tell you when.

776
00:41:00,040 --> 00:41:02,140
记住，你从没见过它，更没碰过它  
Remember, you never saw it, you never even touched it, 

777
00:41:02,140 --> 00:41:03,170
明白吗？
you understand?

778
00:41:02,840 --> 00:41:05,430
-我不是傻瓜      -好的，他何时搭火车？  
I'm not a fool. Okay. When is he leaving on the train?

779
00:41:05,510 --> 00:41:06,980
-问题就在这，他不去了     -什么？ 
That's just it. He isn't going. What?

780
00:41:07,040 --> 00:41:08,940
我一直想说的就是这事，行程取消了
That's what I've been trying to tell you. The trip is off.

781
00:41:09,010 --> 00:41:10,600
发生什么事？ 
What happened?

782
00:41:12,210 --> 00:41:15,180
先生，可以帮我拿那包婴儿食品吗？ 
Mister, could you reach me that package of baby food?

783
00:41:15,250 --> 00:41:16,910
上面那一包？
That one up there?

784
00:41:18,850 --> 00:41:22,690
真不懂干吗老把我需要的放顶层
I don't know why they always put what I want on the top shelf.

785
00:41:24,490 --> 00:41:25,650
继续说，我在听
Go ahead. I'm listening.

786
00:41:25,730 --> 00:41:28,090
他从油井掉下，腿断了，打了石膏
He had a fall-down at the well. Broke his leg. It's in a cast.

787
00:41:28,160 --> 00:41:30,890
-腿断了？     -现在怎么办，沃特？  
Broke his leg? What do we do now, Walter?

788
00:41:31,000 --> 00:41:33,590
-只有等了     -等什么？  
Nothing. We just wait. Wait for what?

789
00:41:33,670 --> 00:41:35,140
等他能搭火车
Until he can take the train.

790
00:41:35,200 --> 00:41:36,430
我说过必须是火车
I told you it's got to be the train.

791
00:41:36,510 --> 00:41:37,840
但我们不能等， 我受不了了
But we can't wait. I can't go on like this.

792
00:41:37,910 --> 00:41:39,100
听着，我们不能只图快
Look, we're not gonna grab a hammer 

793
00:41:39,100 --> 00:41:40,900
不能拿个锤子就把他砸死
and do it quick, just to get it over with.

794
00:41:40,980 --> 00:41:43,740
-还有其他办法    -我们不用其他方法
There are other ways. We're not gonna do it other ways.

795
00:41:43,810 --> 00:41:44,900
但我们不能就此拉倒
But we can't leave it like this.

796
00:41:44,980 --> 00:41:46,040
如果他发现意外险的事
What do you suppose would happen 

797
00:41:46,050 --> 00:41:47,920
你觉得会发生什么？
if he found out about the accident policy?

798
00:41:47,980 --> 00:41:50,040
很多事，但比站在死刑场上好
Plenty. But not as bad as sitting in that death house.

799
00:41:50,120 --> 00:41:51,750
别这么说话  
Don't ever talk like that. 

800
00:41:51,750 --> 00:41:52,920
别就此失去理智，就这样
Don't let's start losing our heads, that's all.

801
00:41:52,990 --> 00:41:55,180
不是理智，我们在失去勇气
It's not our heads. It's our nerve we're losing.

802
00:41:59,090 --> 00:42:00,430
借过
Excuse me.

803
00:42:03,530 --> 00:42:05,120
我们一定要做的完美，我一直在说
We're gonna do it right. That's all I said.

804
00:42:05,200 --> 00:42:06,690
是等待让我难过
It's the waiting that's getting me.

805
00:42:06,770 --> 00:42:08,240
我也一样难过，宝贝
It's getting me just as bad, baby.

806
00:42:08,300 --> 00:42:11,330
-但我们一定得等     -也许是，但，沃特...
But we've got to wait. Maybe we have, Walter, only...

807
00:42:11,410 --> 00:42:14,870
没有你日子很难过，好像我们之间有一道墙
it's so tough without you. It's like a wall between us.

808
00:42:16,680 --> 00:42:19,980
我得走了，宝贝。我无时无刻不想念你
I better go, baby. I'm thinking of you every minute.

809
00:42:26,020 --> 00:42:29,580
那之后整整一周，我再没见她
After that, a full week went by and I didn't see her once.

810
00:42:29,690 --> 00:42:33,150
我试着忘记她，和整个计划
I tried to keep my mind off her and off the whole idea.

811
00:42:33,260 --> 00:42:34,530
我不断告诉自己
I kept telling myself 

812
00:42:34,530 --> 00:42:36,130
是我的所谓宿命
that maybe those Fates they say watch over you...

813
00:42:36,200 --> 00:42:39,930
弄断了他的腿，给我一条出路
had gotten together and broken his leg to give me a way out.

814
00:42:40,040 --> 00:42:43,990
那天是6月15日，你或者记得，基斯
Then it was the 15th of June. You may remember that date, Keyes.

815
00:42:45,410 --> 00:42:48,740
你下午3点左右来我的办公室
You came into my office around 3:00 in the afternoon.

816
00:42:49,410 --> 00:42:50,710
嗨，基斯
Hello, Keyes.

817
00:42:50,780 --> 00:42:52,010
我刚从诺顿办公室回来
I just came from Norton's office.

818
00:42:52,080 --> 00:42:53,570
半年度营业报告公布了
The semiannual sales records are out.

819
00:42:53,650 --> 00:42:55,100
你是最佳销售员，沃特  
You're high man, Walter. 

820
00:42:55,100 --> 00:42:56,550
连续第二次了，恭喜
That's twice in a row. Congratulations.

821
00:42:56,620 --> 00:42:59,320
-谢谢    有兴趣喝一杯吗？  
Thanks. How would you like a cheap drink?

822
00:42:59,390 --> 00:43:01,880
有兴趣减薪50元吗?  
How would you like a $50 cut in salary?

823
00:43:01,960 --> 00:43:04,220
-我应该现在就笑还是等等？   -我说真的
Do I laugh now or wait till it gets funny? No, I'm serious.

824
00:43:04,290 --> 00:43:06,030
我刚跟诺顿谈过  
I've just been talking to Norton. 

825
00:43:06,030 --> 00:43:07,590
我的文件堆积如山
Too much stuff piling up on my desk.

826
00:43:07,660 --> 00:43:08,990
工作压力太大
Too much pressure on my nerves.

827
00:43:09,060 --> 00:43:11,090
半晚上在辗转反侧
I spend half the night walking up and down in my bed.

828
00:43:11,170 --> 00:43:13,070
我得有个助手，于是想到你
I've got to have an assistant and I thought of you.

829
00:43:13,140 --> 00:43:14,530
我？为什么找我？  
Me? Why pick on me?

830
00:43:14,600 --> 00:43:17,130
那，我有个离奇的想法，觉得你很合适
Well, because I've got a crazy idea you might be good at the job.

831
00:43:17,210 --> 00:43:18,610
是很离奇，我是个销售员
That's crazy, all right. I'm a salesman.

832
00:43:18,670 --> 00:43:21,870
对 ，你长袖善舞 ，能文能武
Yeah. A peddler, a gladhander, a backslapper.

833
00:43:22,440 --> 00:43:23,710
做销售员实在太浪费
You're too good to be a salesman.

834
00:43:23,780 --> 00:43:25,910
没人做销售员会浪费
Nobody's too good to be a salesman. Phooey!

835
00:43:25,980 --> 00:43:28,070
你们的工作就是按门铃  
All you guys do is just ring doorbells 

836
00:43:28,070 --> 00:43:29,470
说一番机械套话
and dish out a smooth line of monkey talk.

837
00:43:29,550 --> 00:43:31,710
你是介意降薪50，是吗？ 
What's troubling you is that $50 cut, isn't it?

838
00:43:31,790 --> 00:43:33,310
-谁都会介意     -听着，沃特
Well, that'd trouble anybody. Now look, Walter.

839
00:43:33,390 --> 00:43:36,360
我说的工作需要头脑与正义感
The job I'm talking about takes brains and integrity.

840
00:43:36,430 --> 00:43:38,330
和比50个销售员加起来还多的胆量
It takes more guts than there is in 50 salesmen.

841
00:43:38,390 --> 00:43:39,520
这是保险业中的热门
It's the hottest job in the business.

842
00:43:39,600 --> 00:43:40,820
对，但还是个办公室工作
Yeah, but it's still a desk job.

843
00:43:40,900 --> 00:43:43,020
-我不想被困在办公室     -办公室工作？
I don't want to be nailed to a desk. Desk job?

844
00:43:43,100 --> 00:43:44,690
你就看到这些？  
Is that all you can see in it?

845
00:43:44,770 --> 00:43:47,740
只有朝九晚五放你屁股的破椅子？
Just a hard chair to park your pants on from 9:00 to 5:00, huh?

846
00:43:47,800 --> 00:43:49,160
只有大堆文件...
Just a pile of papers to shuffle around, 

847
00:43:49,160 --> 00:43:50,530
几根铅笔...
and five sharp pencils...

848
00:43:50,610 --> 00:43:53,180
算数的黑板...
and a scratch pad to make figures on, 

849
00:43:53,180 --> 00:43:54,980
胡乱的涂鸦
maybe a little doodling on the side.

850
00:43:55,040 --> 00:43:57,070
但，我不是这么看的，沃特
Well, that's not the way I look at it, Walter.

851
00:43:57,150 --> 00:44:00,040
我说，索赔员是外科医生  
To me, a claims man is a surgeon, 

852
00:44:00,040 --> 00:44:01,240
办公桌是手术台
that desk is an operating table...

853
00:44:01,320 --> 00:44:04,150
铅笔是手术刀和骨锯
and those pencils are scalpels and bone chisels.

854
00:44:04,220 --> 00:44:05,800
那些纸不只是
And those papers are not just 

855
00:44:05,800 --> 00:44:08,020
赔偿声明、表格和数据
forms and statistics and claims for compensation.

856
00:44:08,090 --> 00:44:11,220
他们是活生生的，充满戏剧性
They're alive. They're packed with drama...

857
00:44:11,430 --> 00:44:13,620
充满纠结的希望和扭曲的梦想
with twisted hopes and crooked dreams.

858
00:44:13,700 --> 00:44:16,930
索赔员，沃特，是医生、侦探和...
A claims man, Walter, is a doctor and a bloodhound and a...

859
00:44:19,400 --> 00:44:21,530
谁？好，等一下
Who? Okay, hold on a minute.

860
00:44:21,800 --> 00:44:23,360
索赔员是医生  
A claims man is a doctor 

861
00:44:23,360 --> 00:44:24,930
侦探、警察、法官、陪审团
and a bloodhound and a cop and a judge and a jury...

862
00:44:25,010 --> 00:44:26,700
和告解神父，集于一身
and a father confessor, all in one.

863
00:44:26,780 --> 00:44:28,330
而你想告诉我你没兴趣？ 
And you want to tell me you're not interested?

864
00:44:28,410 --> 00:44:29,570
你不想用脑袋工作？ 
You don't want to work with your brains?

865
00:44:29,650 --> 00:44:31,700
你只想用手按门铃来工作？
All you want to work is with your finger on the doorbell...

866
00:44:31,780 --> 00:44:35,310
就为一周多几块钱？   有个女人找你
for a few bucks more a week. There's a dame on your phone.

867
00:44:35,380 --> 00:44:37,910
-我是沃特.奈夫     -我必须打给你，沃特
Walter Neff speaking. I had to call you, Walter.

868
00:44:37,990 --> 00:44:39,350
事关紧急，有人在旁边吗？  
It's very urgent. Are you with somebody?

869
00:44:40,860 --> 00:44:43,980
是，我是。我再打给你好吗，麦姬 ？ 
Yes, I am. Can't I call you back, Margie?

870
00:44:44,690 --> 00:44:47,890
不行，我没时间，很紧急
No, you can't. I've only got a minute. It can't wait.

871
00:44:47,960 --> 00:44:51,260
听着，他今晚出发，坐火车，你在听吗？  
Listen. He's going tonight. On the train. Are you listening?

872
00:44:51,330 --> 00:44:53,930
-沃特？     -我在听，麦姬
Walter? Yeah. I'm listening, Margie.

873
00:44:54,640 --> 00:44:57,160
-有话快说好吗？    -他拄拐杖
Only, make it snappy, will you? He's on crutches.

874
00:44:57,240 --> 00:44:58,070
医生说
The doctor says 

875
00:44:58,070 --> 00:45:00,570
如果小心点他能去，活动对他有好处
he can go if he's careful. The change will do him good.

876
00:45:00,640 --> 00:45:03,410
太好了，沃特，如你所愿，坐火车
It's wonderful, Walter. Just the way you wanted it, on a train.

877
00:45:03,480 --> 00:45:06,040
而且拄拐杖会更有利，是吗？  
Only with the crutches it makes it much better, doesn't it?

878
00:45:06,120 --> 00:45:08,550
对，好多了
Yeah. Yeah, that's 100% better.

879
00:45:10,150 --> 00:45:11,450
稍等一下好吗？
Hold the line a minute, will you?

880
00:45:11,520 --> 00:45:13,210
基斯，等会我去找你？  
Keyes, suppose I join you in your office? 

881
00:45:13,210 --> 00:45:14,250
没关系，我等你
That's all right. I'll wait.

882
00:45:14,320 --> 00:45:16,760
只是告诉她别说上一天
Only tell her not to take all day.

883
00:45:18,530 --> 00:45:19,650
继续
Go ahead.

884
00:45:20,000 --> 00:45:23,060
是格伦戴尔10点15分的火车，我开车送他
It's the 10:15 from Glendale. I'm driving him.

885
00:45:23,130 --> 00:45:24,960
还是那条黑暗的街道，是吗？ 
It's still the same dark street, isn't it?

886
00:45:25,030 --> 00:45:28,300
-信号是三声喇叭     -好，还有事吗？  
And the signal is three honks on the horn. Okay. Anything else?

887
00:45:29,070 --> 00:45:30,100
没有
No.

888
00:45:30,370 --> 00:45:31,360
哦...
Oh, uh...

889
00:45:31,940 --> 00:45:33,530
你选了什么颜色？ 
what color did you pick?

890
00:45:33,610 --> 00:45:36,510
蓝色，海军蓝。 他左腿打石膏
Blue. Navy blue. And the cast is on his left leg.

891
00:45:37,250 --> 00:45:38,440
恩
Mmm-hmm.

892
00:45:38,980 --> 00:45:40,510
好，很适合我
Yeah, that suits me fine.

893
00:45:40,580 --> 00:45:42,850
事到临头了，沃特，我浑身发抖
This is it, Walter. I'm shaking like a leaf.

894
00:45:42,920 --> 00:45:45,940
但我们会彻头彻尾
But it's straight down the line for both of us.

895
00:45:46,020 --> 00:45:48,150
-我爱你，沃特。   -再见
I love you, Walter. Goodbye.

896
00:45:50,230 --> 00:45:52,130
-对不起，基斯      -怎么了？
Sorry, Keyes. What's the matter?

897
00:45:52,190 --> 00:45:54,920
有女孩追你吗？有新欢？还是说与我无关？
Dames chasing you again? Or still? Or is it none of my business?

898
00:45:55,000 --> 00:45:56,860
如果我告诉你是个客人...
If I told you it was a customer...

899
00:45:57,030 --> 00:45:59,090
麦姬，我猜她喝酒对瓶吹
Margie. I bet she drinks from the bottle.

900
00:45:59,170 --> 00:46:01,030
你为什么不安定下来结婚，沃特？ 
Why don't you settle down and get married, Walter?

901
00:46:01,100 --> 00:46:05,160
-你为什么不呢？      -我曾经差点，很久以前
Why don't you, for instance? I almost did, once. Long time ago.

902
00:46:05,240 --> 00:46:07,000
基斯，我得打电话给客人
Now look, Keyes, I've got to call on a prospect.

903
00:46:07,080 --> 00:46:09,600
我俩连教堂都选好了
Even had the church picked out, the dame and I.

904
00:46:09,680 --> 00:46:11,910
她有一件带荷叶边的丝裙
She had a white satin dress with flounces on it.

905
00:46:11,980 --> 00:46:14,810
我正在去珠宝店买戒指的路上
I was on my way to the jewelry store to buy the ring.

906
00:46:14,880 --> 00:46:17,480
然后这里突然有个小人开始活动
And then suddenly that little man in here started working on me.

907
00:46:17,550 --> 00:46:19,080
所以你回去把她调查一番？
So you went back and had her investigated?

908
00:46:19,150 --> 00:46:21,590
对，事情终于水落石出
Yeah. And the stuff that came out...

909
00:46:22,560 --> 00:46:24,920
她自从16岁就开始染发
She'd been dyeing her hair ever since she was 16.

910
00:46:24,990 --> 00:46:27,520
她家有个躁郁症患者，她母亲那边
There was a manic depressive in her family, on her mother's side.

911
00:46:27,600 --> 00:46:29,220
她已经有个丈夫
She already had one husband.

912
00:46:29,300 --> 00:46:31,390
他是巴尔的摩的职业台球手...
He was a professional pool player in Baltimore.

913
00:46:31,470 --> 00:46:33,530
-至于她哥...       -我大致明白了
And as for her brother... I get the general idea.

914
00:46:33,600 --> 00:46:35,710
她是众多骗子中的一个  
She was a tramp from a long line of tramps. 

915
00:46:35,710 --> 00:46:37,230
对，好了，好了
Yeah. All right, all right.

916
00:46:37,310 --> 00:46:40,040
-那我怎么对诺顿说？关于我说的那份工作？  
Now what do I say to Norton? What about this job I want you for?

917
00:46:40,110 --> 00:46:41,670
我想我不想要，基斯
I don't think I want it, Keyes.

918
00:46:41,740 --> 00:46:44,230
-但非常感谢      -好吧
Thanks just the same. Fair enough.

919
00:46:45,180 --> 00:46:47,410
你得明白，我选择你，
Only get this, I picked you for the job...

920
00:46:47,480 --> 00:46:49,640
不是认为你很聪明
not because I think you're so darn smart...

921
00:46:49,720 --> 00:46:51,100
而是因为我以为你没有...
but because I thought you were a shade less dumb 

922
00:46:51,100 --> 00:46:53,050
表面看起来那么笨
than the rest of the outfit.

923
00:47:00,230 --> 00:47:03,220
大概我错了。 你并不聪明，沃特
Guess I was wrong. You're not smarter, Walter.

924
00:47:03,470 --> 00:47:05,590
只是比较高
You're just a little taller.

925
00:47:16,510 --> 00:47:17,880
是的，基斯
Yes, Keyes.

926
00:47:17,950 --> 00:47:21,540
我说到的宿命只是拖延了我
Those Fates I was talking about had only been stalling me off.

927
00:47:21,620 --> 00:47:24,980
现在它已启动开关，运转齿轮
Now they had thrown the switch. The gears had meshed.

928
00:47:25,090 --> 00:47:27,720
用来思考的时间已用尽
The time for thinking had all run out.

929
00:47:28,460 --> 00:47:29,890
我希望从始至终
I wanted my movements accounted 

930
00:47:29,890 --> 00:47:32,190
我的行动都无懈可击
for up to the last possible moment.

931
00:47:32,260 --> 00:47:34,030
所以我离开办公室时  
So when I left the office 

932
00:47:34,030 --> 00:47:36,390
把计算本放到办公桌上，假装遗落
I put my rate book on the desk as if I had forgotten it.

933
00:47:36,470 --> 00:47:38,490
那是我的伏笔之一
That was part of my alibi.

934
00:47:39,940 --> 00:47:42,670
从此开始，只需按照时间表...
From here on, it was a question of following the timetable...

935
00:47:42,740 --> 00:47:43,760
按部就班
move by move.

936
00:47:45,610 --> 00:47:48,700
我大约7点到家，停车入库
I got home about 7:00 and drove right into the garage.

937
00:47:48,780 --> 00:47:51,710
这又是制造不在场证明的伏笔
This was another item to establish my alibi.

938
00:47:53,080 --> 00:47:55,380
-嗨，奈夫先生     -你好，查理
Hi, Mr. Neff. Hello, Charlie.

939
00:47:55,450 --> 00:47:57,280
帮我洗车好吗？
How about giving the heap a wash job?

940
00:47:57,350 --> 00:47:58,510
你何时要？  
How soon you gonna want it?

941
00:47:58,590 --> 00:47:59,990
前面有几辆了
I got a couple cars ahead of you.

942
00:48:00,060 --> 00:48:01,580
随你方便，查理
Any time you get to it, Charlie.

943
00:48:01,660 --> 00:48:03,890
-晚上我待在家     -好
I'm staying in tonight. Okay.

944
00:48:03,990 --> 00:48:05,960
回公寓后我打给路.舒华兹...
Up in my apartment I called Lou Schwartz...

945
00:48:06,030 --> 00:48:08,330
我办公室的另一销售员
one of the salesmen that shared my office.

946
00:48:08,400 --> 00:48:09,760
他住在威斯伍德  
He lived in Westwood, 

947
00:48:09,760 --> 00:48:11,800
所以那算长途电话，会有记录
so it was a toll call and there'd be a record of it.

948
00:48:11,870 --> 00:48:14,170
我告诉他我忘带计算本，我需要...
I told him I'd forgotten my rate book and needed some dope...

949
00:48:14,240 --> 00:48:17,170
一些我在弄的公债事务的资料...
on the public liability bond I was figuring.

950
00:48:17,310 --> 00:48:18,430
我换上...
I changed into 

951
00:48:18,430 --> 00:48:21,070
迪崔克森将会穿的海军蓝衣服
a navy blue suit like Dietrichson was going to wear.

952
00:48:21,140 --> 00:48:24,240
路.舒华兹回电，给了我很多数据
Lou Schwartz called me back and gave me a lot of figures.

953
00:48:24,310 --> 00:48:26,750
我将毛巾，胶带装进衣兜
I stuffed a hand towel and a roll of adhesive into my pockets...

954
00:48:26,820 --> 00:48:28,810
可以用来做成...
so I could fake something 

955
00:48:28,810 --> 00:48:30,810
像断腿上石膏的东西
that looked like a cast on a broken leg.

956
00:48:30,890 --> 00:48:32,910
接着，我在电话里插了张卡片
Next, I stuck a card inside the telephone box...

957
00:48:32,990 --> 00:48:35,820
如果铃响，卡片就会掉
so that it would fall down if the bell rang.

958
00:48:35,890 --> 00:48:39,380
那样我就知道我不在时是否有来电
That way I'd know if anybody had called me while I was away.

959
00:48:39,460 --> 00:48:41,210
门铃也如法炮制
Then I did the same thing to the doorbell 

960
00:48:41,210 --> 00:48:43,660
以防有人上门找我
in case anybody came to see me.

961
00:48:44,170 --> 00:48:47,800
我走保洁楼梯离开住所，没人看见我
I left the apartment by the service stairs. Nobody saw me.

962
00:48:48,800 --> 00:48:52,070
我步行从公寓走到迪崔克森家
I walked all the way from my apartment to the Dietrichson house.

963
00:48:52,140 --> 00:48:53,510
我不想搭巴士
I didn't want to take the bus...

964
00:48:53,580 --> 00:48:55,670
因为有可能...
because there was always the chance 

965
00:48:55,670 --> 00:48:57,240
有人会记得在巴士上见过我
that someone might remember seeing me on it.

966
00:48:57,310 --> 00:48:59,300
我谨慎到这种程度
I was being that careful.

967
00:48:59,720 --> 00:49:02,310
我又问到金银花的味道
I could smell that honeysuckle again.

968
00:49:02,420 --> 00:49:05,580
只是这次更加强烈，而这次是晚上
Only it was even stronger, now that it was night.

969
00:49:09,990 --> 00:49:13,190
我尽可能安静的打开车库门
I slid the garage door open as quietly as I could.

970
00:49:13,530 --> 00:49:16,590
她已按我说的，将车头朝外停好
She'd backed the sedan in, just the way I told her to.

971
00:49:16,670 --> 00:49:18,160
我认为这样停更安全
I'd figured it was safer that way...

972
00:49:18,230 --> 00:49:21,290
以防他在她将车开出前就上车
in case he got into the car before she drove it out.

973
00:49:21,370 --> 00:49:23,670
我进到车后部
I got into the back of the car.

974
00:49:23,740 --> 00:49:26,210
躺在地上等待
I lay there on the floor and waited.

975
00:49:26,270 --> 00:49:27,590
我一直在想着...
All the time I was thinking about 

976
00:49:27,590 --> 00:49:29,370
通往火车站的黑暗街道
that dark street on the way to the station...

977
00:49:29,440 --> 00:49:31,240
我的动手之处...
where I was to do it...

978
00:49:31,310 --> 00:49:34,080
以及作为信号的三声喇叭
and the three honks on the horn that were to be the signal.

979
00:49:34,150 --> 00:49:36,550
十分钟后，他们下来了
About 10 minutes later they came down.

980
00:49:36,620 --> 00:49:38,350
-还好吗，亲爱的？    -是的，还好
All right, honey? Yeah, I'm all right.

981
00:49:38,420 --> 00:49:40,850
我马上把车开出来
I'll have the car out in a second.

982
00:50:17,660 --> 00:50:20,960
-慢慢来，还有很多时间     -对
Take it easy, honey. We've got lots of time. Yeah.

983
00:50:40,320 --> 00:50:42,410
牢记医生的话。如果你不小心...
Remember what the doctor said. If you get careless...

984
00:50:42,480 --> 00:50:44,210
以后会成为长短腿
you might end up with a shorter leg.

985
00:50:44,290 --> 00:50:48,090
那又怎样？我可以打断另一条让它们一样长
So what? I could break the other one and match them up again.

986
00:50:48,460 --> 00:50:50,950
摆脱我让你感觉不错，是吗？  
It makes you feel pretty good to get away from me, doesn't it?

987
00:50:51,030 --> 00:50:54,720
只是四天，最迟周一我就回来
It's only for four days. I'll be back Monday at the latest.

988
00:51:10,810 --> 00:51:14,110
不是这条街，干嘛在这转弯？  
This is not the right street. Why did you turn here?

989
00:51:18,050 --> 00:51:20,180
你这是干吗？ 
What are you doing that for?

990
00:51:21,190 --> 00:51:23,660
按喇叭干吗？  
What are you honking the horn for?

991
00:52:23,820 --> 00:52:25,810
你应付搬运工和售票员
You take care of the redcap and the conductor.

992
00:52:25,890 --> 00:52:28,220
-不用担心      -尽量离我远点
Don't worry. Keep away from me as much as you can.

993
00:52:28,290 --> 00:52:29,570
告诉他们我不想被帮助  
Tell them I don't want to be helped. 

994
00:52:29,570 --> 00:52:30,760
我说过，不用担心，沃特
I said, don't worry, Walter.

995
00:52:30,830 --> 00:52:33,060
火车一走你就出发，
You start as soon as the train leaves.

996
00:52:33,130 --> 00:52:34,370
到达冶炼厂后，  
When you get to the refinery, 

997
00:52:34,370 --> 00:52:35,790
离开公路开上土路
turn off the highway onto the dirt road.

998
00:52:35,860 --> 00:52:37,420
从那开始整五分之四英里...
From there it's exactly eight-tenths of a mile...

999
00:52:37,500 --> 00:52:38,930
就到铁轨旁的垃圾场。记住  
to the dump beside the tracks. Remember.

1000
00:52:39,000 --> 00:52:41,530
-我全都记得。    -不要超速
I remember everything. No speeding.

1001
00:52:42,870 --> 00:52:45,570
你不想被警察截停，而他在后面
You don't want any cops stopping you with him in the back.

1002
00:52:45,640 --> 00:52:48,010
沃特，我们排练过很多次了。
Walter, we've been through all that so many times.

1003
00:52:48,080 --> 00:52:50,340
离开公路时，关闭所有灯光
When you leave the highway, turn off all your lights.

1004
00:52:50,450 --> 00:52:52,540
我会到后面的观景台
I'll be back on the observation platform.

1005
00:52:52,610 --> 00:52:55,280
我会在预定位置附近跳车
I'll drop off as close to the spot as I can.

1006
00:52:55,350 --> 00:52:58,410
等火车经过后，闪两次灯
Let the train pass, then dim your lights twice.

1007
00:53:00,960 --> 00:53:03,340
-旧金山，女士？    -9车厢，11室  
San Francisco train, lady? Car 9, section 11. 

1008
00:53:03,340 --> 00:53:03,890
只有我丈夫
Just my husband.

1009
00:53:03,960 --> 00:53:06,450
9车厢，11室？这边请
Car 9, section 11? This way please.

1010
00:53:14,540 --> 00:53:16,470
谢谢。我丈夫不希望别人帮忙
Thank you. My husband doesn't like to be helped.

1011
00:53:16,540 --> 00:53:18,400
8车厢。在那里
Car number 8. Up there.

1012
00:53:23,710 --> 00:53:27,310
9车厢，11室。 谢谢
Car 9, section 11. Thank you.

1013
00:53:29,920 --> 00:53:32,320
这是车票，一定要小心腿
Here're the tickets. Take good care of yourself with that leg.

1014
00:53:32,390 --> 00:53:33,750
好，你开车回家要小心
Yeah. You take it easy driving home.

1015
00:53:33,820 --> 00:53:37,260
-我会想你的，宝贝    -11室，先生
I'll miss you, honey. Section 11, sir.

1016
00:53:39,160 --> 00:53:41,030
-全部登车！    -谢谢
All aboard! Thank you.

1017
00:53:41,130 --> 00:53:43,260
-再见，亲爱的      -全部登车！
Goodbye, honey. All aboard!

1018
00:53:49,070 --> 00:53:50,700
好运，亲爱的
Good luck, honey.

1019
00:53:59,310 --> 00:54:00,910
服务员，帮我弄好铺位好吗？
Porter, will you make up my berth right away?

1020
00:54:00,980 --> 00:54:02,040
是，先生
Yes, sir.

1021
00:54:02,120 --> 00:54:03,810
我去后面观景台抽一口烟
I'm going back to the observation car for a smoke.

1022
00:54:03,890 --> 00:54:05,580
这边，先生
Right this way, sir.

1023
00:54:37,420 --> 00:54:38,890
要椅子吗？ 
Like a chair?

1024
00:54:41,090 --> 00:54:44,020
不，谢谢，我想站一下
No, thanks. I'd rather stand.

1025
00:54:45,430 --> 00:54:48,830
-你去很远吗？     -帕洛阿尔托
You going far? Palo Alto.

1026
00:54:49,700 --> 00:54:50,760
我叫杰克逊
My name's Jackson.

1027
00:54:50,830 --> 00:54:54,030
我要一路去梅德福，俄勒岗州梅德福
I'm going all the way to Medford. Medford, Oregon.

1028
00:54:54,440 --> 00:54:56,430
我曾断过胳膊
I had a broken arm once.

1029
00:54:56,940 --> 00:55:00,240
石膏令人奇痒难忍，是不是？  
That darn cast itches something fierce, doesn't it?

1030
00:55:00,340 --> 00:55:02,640
我的让我快疯了
I thought I'd go crazy with mine.

1031
00:55:02,710 --> 00:55:06,770
帕尔阿尔托是个不错的小镇，你是斯坦福的？  
Palo Alto's a nice little town. You a Stanford man?

1032
00:55:07,580 --> 00:55:11,780
-我以前是    -我猜你落下东西了
I used to be. I'll bet you left something behind.

1033
00:55:12,550 --> 00:55:13,950
我经常如此
I always do.

1034
00:55:14,120 --> 00:55:15,430
我的雪茄盒  
My cigar case. 

1035
00:55:15,430 --> 00:55:17,490
可能落在我车厢里的外衣里
I guess I left it in my overcoat back in the section.

1036
00:55:17,560 --> 00:55:20,890
你想自己卷支烟吗，未请教...
Would you care to roll yourself a cigarette, Mister...

1037
00:55:20,960 --> 00:55:21,950
迪崔克森
Dietrichson.

1038
00:55:22,460 --> 00:55:24,960
不，谢谢，我想抽雪茄
No thanks, I really prefer a cigar.

1039
00:55:25,670 --> 00:55:28,860
也许服务员可以...，好吧，我可以给你拿来
Maybe the porter could... Well, I could get your cigars for you.

1040
00:55:28,940 --> 00:55:32,300
-很乐意，迪崔克森先生     -希望不会麻烦到你
Be glad to, Mr. Dietrichson. If it's not too much trouble.

1041
00:55:32,370 --> 00:55:35,580
-9车厢，11室    -9车厢，11室
Car 9, section 11. Car 9, section 11. 

1042
00:55:35,580 --> 00:55:36,170
乐意效劳
With pleasure.

1043
00:56:20,460 --> 00:56:22,010
好了， 必须快点
Okay. This has gotta be fast.

1044
00:56:22,090 --> 00:56:25,580
这儿，拿着他的帽子，去前边铁轨拾回拐杖
Here, take his hat. Pick up the crutches back on the tracks.

1045
00:56:54,860 --> 00:56:56,720
好了，宝贝。 行了
Okay, baby. That's it.

1046
00:57:55,050 --> 00:57:56,810
好的，走吧
All right. Let's go.

1047
00:58:06,690 --> 00:58:08,530
回去路上，我们又排练一次...
On the way back, we went over once more...

1048
00:58:08,600 --> 00:58:10,030
审讯时她该如何表现...
what she was to do at the inquest...

1049
00:58:10,100 --> 00:58:13,830
如果有审讯的话，以及保险的事，肯定会提及
if they had one, and about the insurance, when that came up.

1050
00:58:13,970 --> 00:58:15,330
我曾担心她可能会有些崩溃，
I was afraid she might go to pieces a little, 

1051
00:58:15,330 --> 00:58:17,030
在我们行事完毕后
now that we had done it.

1052
00:58:17,110 --> 00:58:19,250
但她表现完美，毫不紧张  
But she was perfect. No nerves. 

1053
00:58:19,250 --> 00:58:21,700
没一滴泪，甚至眼都没眨 
Not a tear, not even a blink of the eyes.

1054
00:58:22,710 --> 00:58:25,770
她在离我公寓一个街区外放下我
She dropped me a block from my apartment house.

1055
00:58:26,580 --> 00:58:30,040
沃特，怎么了？你不打算吻我吗？ 
Walter, what's the matter? Aren't you going to kiss me?

1056
00:58:34,960 --> 00:58:37,580
彻头彻尾，不是吗？  
It's straight down the line, isn't it?

1057
00:58:42,330 --> 00:58:45,790
-我爱你，沃特     -我爱你，宝贝
I love you, Walter. I love you, baby.

1058
00:58:58,950 --> 00:59:00,700
11点2分了  
It was two minutes past 11:00, 

1059
00:59:00,700 --> 00:59:02,710
我又从保洁楼梯上楼
as I went up the service stairs again.

1060
00:59:02,780 --> 00:59:05,000
这次也没人看见我  
Nobody saw me this time either. 

1061
00:59:05,000 --> 00:59:06,780
我检查了门铃、电话
In the apartment I checked the bells.

1062
00:59:06,850 --> 00:59:09,850
卡片没动，没人来电，没人上门
The cards hadn't moved. No calls. No visitors.

1063
00:59:11,360 --> 00:59:13,340
然后我又换了衣服  
Then I changed my clothes again. 

1064
00:59:13,340 --> 00:59:15,320
还剩最后一件事
That left one last thing to do.

1065
00:59:16,300 --> 00:59:20,290
我得下去车房。我想让查理再看到我。
I had to go down to the garage. I wanted Charlie to see me again.

1066
00:59:26,980 --> 00:59:29,880
你又要用车吗？我还没洗好
You gonna use your car, after all? I'm not quite through.

1067
00:59:29,940 --> 00:59:31,810
没关系，查理
Well, that's all right, Charlie.

1068
00:59:31,880 --> 00:59:33,970
只是去杂货店买点吃的
Just going up to the drugstore to get something to eat.

1069
00:59:34,050 --> 00:59:36,030
工作了一整夜  
Been working upstairs all night. 

1070
00:59:36,030 --> 00:59:37,020
肚子有点抗议啊
My stomach's getting a little sore at me.

1071
00:59:37,090 --> 00:59:38,680
是的，先生
Yes, sir, Mr. Neff.

1072
00:59:40,620 --> 00:59:42,610
事情终于告一段落
That was all there was to it.

1073
00:59:42,690 --> 00:59:45,350
没有错误，没有疏漏
Nothing had slipped, nothing had been overlooked.

1074
00:59:45,430 --> 00:59:47,830
没什么能暴露我们
There was nothing to give us away.

1075
00:59:47,900 --> 00:59:49,450
然而，基斯
And yet, Keyes, 

1076
00:59:49,450 --> 00:59:51,520
当我走向杂货店时...
as I was walking down the street to the drugstore...

1077
00:59:51,600 --> 00:59:55,040
我突然觉得一切都将坍塌
suddenly it came over me that everything would go wrong.

1078
00:59:55,100 --> 00:59:58,300
听来很疯狂，但这是真的，帮帮我
It sounds crazy, Keyes, but it's true, so help me.

1079
00:59:58,470 --> 01:00:00,870
我听不见自己的脚步声
I couldn't hear my own footsteps.

1080
01:00:04,050 --> 01:00:06,280
因为那是死人的脚步
It was the walk of a dead man.

1081
01:00:14,190 --> 01:00:16,750
那是我毕生最漫长的一夜
That was the longest night I ever lived through, Keyes...

1082
01:00:16,820 --> 01:00:18,970
接下来一天更难熬  
and the next day was worse, 

1083
01:00:18,970 --> 01:00:20,690
因事情已经上报纸
when the story had broke in the papers...

1084
01:00:20,760 --> 01:00:22,660
公司的人开始讨论这事
and they started talking about it at the office...

1085
01:00:22,730 --> 01:00:25,960
那天之后，你开始接手
and the day after that, when you started digging into it.

1086
01:00:26,030 --> 01:00:28,390
我将手放进衣兜
I kept my hands in my pockets 

1087
01:00:28,390 --> 01:00:29,970
因为我觉得它们颤抖不已
because I thought they were shaking.

1088
01:00:30,040 --> 01:00:32,270
我带上墨镜，不让人看我眼睛
I put on dark glasses so people couldn't see my eyes.

1089
01:00:32,340 --> 01:00:34,180
然后又摘下来  
And then I took them off again 

1090
01:00:34,180 --> 01:00:36,300
以免他们觉得奇怪
so they wouldn't get to wondering why I wore them.

1091
01:00:36,380 --> 01:00:39,070
我尝试保持冷静，但是...
I tried to hold myself together, but...

1092
01:00:39,410 --> 01:00:42,410
又感觉我的紧张将我撕裂
I could feel my nerves pulling me to pieces.

1093
01:00:45,150 --> 01:00:47,990
-噢，沃特？     -嗨，基斯
Oh, Walter? Hello, Keyes.

1094
01:00:48,260 --> 01:00:50,420
过来，大老板想见我们
Come along. The big boss wants to see us.

1095
01:00:50,490 --> 01:00:52,790
-迪崔克森的案子？    -一定是
The Dietrichson case? Must be.

1096
01:00:52,960 --> 01:00:54,930
-有问题吗？     -他死了
Anything wrong? Well, the guy is dead.

1097
01:00:55,000 --> 01:00:58,030
我们保的险，我们要赔大了  
We had him insured and it's gonna cost us dough. 

1098
01:00:58,030 --> 01:00:58,900
这一直是问题
That's always wrong.

1099
01:00:58,970 --> 01:01:01,230
-他们掌握什么情况了？    -验尸报告
What have they got so far? Autopsy report.

1100
01:01:01,300 --> 01:01:03,110
没有心脏病，没中风  
No heart failure, no apoplexy, 

1101
01:01:03,110 --> 01:01:04,930
或任何疾病原因 
no predisposing medical cause of any kind.

1102
01:01:05,010 --> 01:01:06,870
死于脖子断了
Died of a broken neck.

1103
01:01:07,010 --> 01:01:09,030
-几时审讯？      -早晨审过了
When's the inquest? Had it this morning.

1104
01:01:09,110 --> 01:01:11,170
他的妻女认尸完毕
His wife and daughter made the identification.

1105
01:01:11,250 --> 01:01:12,640
火车职员
The train people 

1106
01:01:12,640 --> 01:01:14,040
及一些乘客说...
and some of the passengers told how he went through...

1107
01:01:14,120 --> 01:01:15,380
他走到了观景台
to the observation car.

1108
01:01:15,450 --> 01:01:19,010
45分钟内就结束了    裁决呢？   意外死亡
It was all over in 45 minutes. Verdict? Accidental death.

1109
01:01:20,620 --> 01:01:22,090
警方认为呢？  
What do the police figure?

1110
01:01:22,160 --> 01:01:24,820
认为他被拐杖绊倒，摔下火车
That he got tangled up in his crutches and fell off the train.

1111
01:01:24,890 --> 01:01:26,520
觉得事实如此
They're satisfied.

1112
01:01:26,590 --> 01:01:29,220
又不是他们赔钱。来吧，沃特
It's not their dough. Come on, Walter.

1113
01:01:30,700 --> 01:01:32,560
好。   非常感谢，各位
All right. Thank you very much, gentlemen.

1114
01:01:32,700 --> 01:01:34,860
我相信法律立场已经很清晰了
I believe the legal position is now clear.

1115
01:01:34,940 --> 01:01:37,270
请待命，我也许需要你们
Please stand by. I may need you later.

1116
01:01:37,340 --> 01:01:40,210
请进，基斯先生，还有你，奈夫先生
Come in, Mr. Keyes. You, too, Mr. Neff.

1117
01:01:44,550 --> 01:01:46,840
你觉得今天暖和的不舒服吗，基斯先生？  
You find this an uncomfortably warm day, Mr. Keyes?

1118
01:01:46,910 --> 01:01:49,910
抱歉，诺顿先生，我不知道这是正式会议
I'm sorry, Mr. Norton, but I didn't know this was formal.

1119
01:01:49,980 --> 01:01:51,350
-两位请坐    -谢谢
Sit down, gentlemen. Thank you.

1120
01:01:51,420 --> 01:01:52,440
有新进展吗？  
Any new developments?

1121
01:01:52,520 --> 01:01:54,220
我刚打长途电话给杰克逊 
I just talked to this Jackson long distance, 

1122
01:01:54,230 --> 01:01:55,150
在俄勒冈，梅德福
up in Medford, Oregon.

1123
01:01:55,220 --> 01:01:56,250
那是谁？ 
Who's Jackson?

1124
01:01:56,320 --> 01:01:57,850
他是最后看见迪崔克森活着的人
He's the last man who saw Dietrichson alive.

1125
01:01:57,930 --> 01:02:00,490
他们一起在观景台，聊天
They were out on the observation platform together, talking.

1126
01:02:00,560 --> 01:02:02,620
迪崔克森想抽雪茄，于是杰克逊回去...
Dietrichson wanted a cigar and so Jackson went back...

1127
01:02:02,700 --> 01:02:04,360
帮迪崔克森拿雪茄盒
to get Dietrichson's cigar case for him.

1128
01:02:04,430 --> 01:02:06,800
他返回观景台时，迪崔克森没了
When he returned to the observation platform, no Dietrichson.

1129
01:02:06,870 --> 01:02:08,730
杰克逊当时没觉得有什么不对
Well, Jackson didn't think anything was wrong until...

1130
01:02:08,800 --> 01:02:10,770
直到电报在圣巴巴拉送至火车
a wire caught up with the train at Santa Barbara.

1131
01:02:10,840 --> 01:02:13,570
他们在伯班克附近的铁轨旁发现迪崔克森的尸体
They found Dietrichson's body on the tracks near Burbank.

1132
01:02:13,640 --> 01:02:16,130
雪茄盒的事很有趣
Very interesting about the cigar case.

1133
01:02:16,210 --> 01:02:18,200
-还有别的吗？     -没什么了
Anything else? No, not much.

1134
01:02:18,280 --> 01:02:19,670
迪崔克森的秘书说
Dietrichson's secretary says 

1135
01:02:19,670 --> 01:02:21,270
她不知道保险的事
she didn't know anything about the policy.

1136
01:02:21,350 --> 01:02:23,030
还有女儿
There's a daughter, 

1137
01:02:23,030 --> 01:02:24,720
但她只记得奈夫和她父亲...
but all she remembers is Neff talking to her father...

1138
01:02:24,790 --> 01:02:27,020
有一晚在他们家中谈过意外险
about accident insurance at their house one night.

1139
01:02:27,090 --> 01:02:28,450
我起初说服不了他
I couldn't sell him at first.

1140
01:02:28,520 --> 01:02:31,460
迪崔克森拒绝了，他说他再考虑
