1300
01:09:55,700 --> 01:09:58,330
-你有什么心事？  -那只断腿
What's on your mind? That broken leg.

1301
01:09:58,870 --> 01:10:01,970
-那人的腿断了     -你在说什么？  
The guy had a broken leg. What are you talking about?

1302
01:10:02,040 --> 01:10:05,570
迪崔克森的事，他有意外险，对吗？
Talking about Dietrichson. He had accident insurance, didn't he?

1303
01:10:05,850 --> 01:10:07,910
-对     -然后他断了腿，对吗？
Yeah. Then he broke his leg, didn't he?

1304
01:10:07,980 --> 01:10:09,920
-那又怎样？    -他却没索赔 
So what? And he didn't put in a claim.

1305
01:10:09,980 --> 01:10:13,750
-他为什么不索赔？为什么？    -你想说什么？  
Why didn't he put in a claim? Why? What are you driving at?

1306
01:10:13,920 --> 01:10:18,720
沃特，我俩小时前吃的饭，现在还在噎着
Walter, I had dinner two hours ago and it stuck half way.

1307
01:10:18,790 --> 01:10:20,490
你的小人儿又开始活动了，是吗？  
That little man of yours is acting up again, huh?

1308
01:10:20,560 --> 01:10:22,890
迪崔克森的案子有问题
There's something wrong with the Dietrichson case.

1309
01:10:22,960 --> 01:10:25,450
为什么？因为他没索赔？
Why? Because he didn't file a claim? 

1310
01:10:25,450 --> 01:10:26,800
也许他只是没时间
Maybe he just didn't have time.

1311
01:10:26,870 --> 01:10:29,860
也许他不知道自己有保险
Maybe he just didn't know that he was insured.

1312
01:10:32,040 --> 01:10:33,530
不 ，不，不会是那样
No. No, that couldn't be it.

1313
01:10:33,610 --> 01:10:35,800
你亲自把保单给他的，是吗？  
You delivered the policy to him personally, didn't you?

1314
01:10:35,880 --> 01:10:36,900
-是的    -拿到他的支票了？
Yeah. You got his check?

1315
01:10:36,980 --> 01:10:38,140
当然
Sure I did.

1316
01:10:38,950 --> 01:10:41,880
-有没有苏打水？    -没有
Got any bicarbonate of soda? No, I haven't.

1317
01:10:42,620 --> 01:10:46,280
沃特，我跟我的小人儿生活26年了
Walter, I've been living with this little man for 26 years.

1318
01:10:46,820 --> 01:10:49,450
他从没令我失望。这案件肯定有问题
And he's never failed me yet. There's got to be something wrong.

1319
01:10:49,520 --> 01:10:51,960
也许诺顿说的对。也许是自杀
Well, maybe Norton was right. Maybe it was suicide.

1320
01:10:52,030 --> 01:10:53,620
不，不是自杀
No. Not suicide.

1321
01:10:54,230 --> 01:10:57,290
-但也不是意外。  -那是什么？  
But not an accident, either. What else?

1322
01:10:57,830 --> 01:10:59,060
听好，沃特
Now look, Walter.

1323
01:10:59,130 --> 01:11:02,100
有人购买了一份如果死在火车上...
A guy takes out an accident policy that's worth $100,000...

1324
01:11:02,170 --> 01:11:03,230
会获赔10万的保险
if he's killed on a train.

1325
01:11:03,300 --> 01:11:05,200
两周后，他死在了火车上
Then two weeks later, he is killed on a train.

1326
01:11:05,270 --> 01:11:07,270
但不是火车事故 
And not in a train accident, mind you, 

1327
01:11:07,270 --> 01:11:09,270
而是从什么观景台摔下来
but falling off some silly observation car.

1328
01:11:09,340 --> 01:11:12,010
你知道这个几率有多高？  
Do you know what the mathematical probability of that is?

1329
01:11:12,080 --> 01:11:14,980
不知道几十亿分之一
One out of I don't know how many billions.

1330
01:11:15,750 --> 01:11:18,540
那人还是断腿的  
And add to that the broken leg. 

1331
01:11:18,540 --> 01:11:20,410
不，不会是表面这个样子
No, it just can't be the way it looks.

1332
01:11:20,960 --> 01:11:24,980
-事情有蹊跷   -例如什么？  
Something has been worked on us. Such as what?

1333
01:11:33,000 --> 01:11:34,190
谋杀？  
Murder?

1334
01:11:34,700 --> 01:11:36,570
你有没有薄荷糖什么的？  
Don't you have any peppermint or something?

1335
01:11:36,640 --> 01:11:39,440
-对不起。要点苏打水？    -不用了
Sorry. Want a little soda water? No, no, no.

1336
01:11:40,810 --> 01:11:41,800
你怀疑谁 ？ 
Who do you suspect?

1337
01:11:41,880 --> 01:11:43,810
也许我喜欢为自己省点事
Maybe I like to make things easy for myself.

1338
01:11:43,880 --> 01:11:45,900
但我总是倾向怀疑受益人
But I always tend to suspect the beneficiary.

1339
01:11:45,980 --> 01:11:47,070
-你是指他妻子？   -对  
You mean the wife? Yeah.

1340
01:11:47,150 --> 01:11:47,790
那个两眼无辜  
That wide-eyed dame 

1341
01:11:47,790 --> 01:11:49,710
对什么都一无所知的妇人
that just didn't know anything about anything.

1342
01:11:49,780 --> 01:11:51,810
你疯了，基斯，她都不在火车上
You're crazy, Keyes. She wasn't even on the train.

1343
01:11:51,890 --> 01:11:53,150
我知道，沃特
I know she wasn't, Walter.

1344
01:11:53,220 --> 01:11:55,450
我没说我知道是怎么干的，或谁干的。。。
I don't claim to know how it was worked, or who worked it...

1345
01:11:55,520 --> 01:11:57,960
但我知道事情的确发生了
but all I know is that it was worked.

1346
01:11:58,030 --> 01:11:59,750
我要去药店了
I've got to get to a drugstore.

1347
01:11:59,830 --> 01:12:02,800
这事感觉就像心里有块大石头
This thing feels like a hunk of concrete inside me.

1348
01:12:02,860 --> 01:12:05,560
-晚安，沃特。  -晚安，基斯
Good night, Walter. Good night, Keyes.

1349
01:12:05,900 --> 01:12:08,830
-明早公司见   -好
See you at the office in the morning. Yeah.

1350
01:12:09,870 --> 01:12:12,460
我本想今晚立刻就对付她
I'd like to move in on her right now, tonight.

1351
01:12:12,540 --> 01:12:15,310
要不是诺顿和他公司政策的那些...
If it wasn't for Norton and his striped-pants ideas 

1352
01:12:15,310 --> 01:12:16,700
条条框框
about company policy...

1353
01:12:16,780 --> 01:12:19,440
我会派警察监视，令她晕头转向
I'd have the police after her so fast it'd make her head spin.

1354
01:12:19,510 --> 01:12:21,070
他们会将她放进榨汁机
They'd put her through the wringer...

1355
01:12:21,150 --> 01:12:23,980
把事情都给榨出来
and, brother, the things they would squeeze out.

1356
01:12:24,050 --> 01:12:26,080
只是你没任何证据去进行，基斯
Only you haven't got a single thing to go on, Keyes.

1357
01:12:26,150 --> 01:12:28,450
不多，只有26年的经验
Not too much. Just 26 years experience...

1358
01:12:28,520 --> 01:12:30,490
所有的百分比
all the percentage there is, 

1359
01:12:30,490 --> 01:12:32,750
以及心里这块大石头
and this hunk of concrete in my stomach.

1360
01:12:34,930 --> 01:12:37,190
能给我一个吗？ 
Can I have one of those things?

1361
01:12:48,040 --> 01:12:50,530
-晚安，基斯     -再见，沃特
Good night, Keyes. So long, Walter.

1362
01:13:03,960 --> 01:13:07,150
-他知道多少？    -他什么也不知道
How much does he know? He doesn't know anything.

1363
01:13:07,800 --> 01:13:09,960
只有他该死的预感
It's those stinking hunches of his.

1364
01:13:10,030 --> 01:13:11,360
但他证明不了什么，是吗？
And he can't prove anything, can he?

1365
01:13:11,430 --> 01:13:15,430
只要我们小心，只要我们暂时别见面
Not if we're careful. Not if we don't see each other for a while.

1366
01:13:17,440 --> 01:13:20,000
-要多久？      -直到风头过去
How long a while? Until this dies down.

1367
01:13:20,070 --> 01:13:21,060
你不了解基斯
You don't know Keyes.

1368
01:13:21,140 --> 01:13:23,200
他一咬住就不会放开
Once he gets his teeth into something, he never lets go.

1369
01:13:23,280 --> 01:13:24,970
他会调查你，派人跟踪你
He'll investigate you, have you shadowed.

1370
01:13:25,050 --> 01:13:27,840
他会从现在起时刻盯着你
He'll watch you every minute from now on.

1371
01:13:27,920 --> 01:13:30,410
-你害怕吗，宝贝？  -我很害怕
You afraid, baby? Yes, I'm afraid.

1372
01:13:31,520 --> 01:13:34,050
不是怕基斯，而是害怕我们  
But not of Keyes. I'm afraid of us. 

1373
01:13:34,050 --> 01:13:35,480
我们已经变了
We're not the same anymore.

1374
01:13:35,560 --> 01:13:37,510
我们干这事是为了在一起  
We did it so we could be together, 

1375
01:13:37,510 --> 01:13:38,720
但这却将我们分开
but instead of that it's pulling us apart.

1376
01:13:38,790 --> 01:13:40,560
-不是吗，沃特？     -你在说什么？  
Isn't it, Walter? What are you talking about?

1377
01:13:40,630 --> 01:13:44,320
而且你并不真在乎我们是否见面
And you don't really care whether we see each other or not.

1378
01:13:45,800 --> 01:13:47,290
别这样说，宝贝
Shut up, baby.

1379
01:13:51,540 --> 01:13:53,940
太平洋保险。午安
Pacific All Risk. Good afternoon.

1380
01:13:56,240 --> 01:13:57,840
你好，奈夫先生
Hello, Mr. Neff.

1381
01:13:58,850 --> 01:14:00,870
-你好     -我是萝拉.迪崔克森
Hello. Lola Dietrichson.

1382
01:14:01,250 --> 01:14:04,180
-你不记得我吗？   -当然记得
Don't you remember me? Yes. Yes, of course.

1383
01:14:04,320 --> 01:14:06,510
我能跟你谈一会儿吗？  
Could I talk with you just a few minutes?

1384
01:14:06,590 --> 01:14:09,020
有没有地方可以单独谈？
Somewhere where we could be alone?

1385
01:14:09,260 --> 01:14:11,450
有，来我的办公室
Oh, yes. Come into my office.

1386
01:14:17,800 --> 01:14:19,960
是关于最近的事吗？ 
Is it something about what happened?

1387
01:14:20,030 --> 01:14:23,630
是，奈夫先生，有关我父亲的死
Yes, Mr. Neff. It's about my father's death.

1388
01:14:24,710 --> 01:14:26,300
我很抱歉，迪崔克森小姐
I'm terribly sorry, Miss Dietrichson.

1389
01:14:30,040 --> 01:14:32,640
路，我可以单独用一会儿办公室吗？ 
Lou, do you mind if I use the office alone for a few minutes?

1390
01:14:32,710 --> 01:14:34,610
没问题，沃特
No. It's all yours, Walter.

1391
01:14:41,590 --> 01:14:43,150
看着我，奈夫先生
Look at me, Mr. Neff.

1392
01:14:43,220 --> 01:14:46,680
我没疯，没歇斯底里，甚至没哭
I'm not crazy. I'm not hysterical. I'm not even crying.

1393
01:14:47,760 --> 01:14:51,220
但我有种事有蹊跷的糟糕感觉
But I have the awful feeling that something is wrong...

1394
01:14:51,530 --> 01:14:55,330
我曾有过这种感觉，在我母亲死时
and I had that same feeling once before, when my mother died.

1395
01:14:55,400 --> 01:14:56,430
你母亲死时？
When your mother died?

1396
01:14:56,500 --> 01:14:58,900
那时我们在箭头湖，六年前了
We were at Lake Arrowhead. That was six years ago.

1397
01:14:58,970 --> 01:14:59,960
我们有栋小屋
We had a cabin there.

1398
01:15:00,040 --> 01:15:03,030
那是一个冬天，天很冷 
It was winter and very cold. 

1399
01:15:03,030 --> 01:15:04,370
我母亲因为肺炎病重
My mother was very sick with pneumonia.

1400
01:15:04,680 --> 01:15:06,410
她有一名护士
She had a nurse with her.

1401
01:15:06,510 --> 01:15:09,510
小屋里就我们三个
There were just the three of us in the cabin.

1402
01:15:09,620 --> 01:15:12,310
有一晚我起床，去到母亲的房间
One night I got up and went into my mother's room.

1403
01:15:12,390 --> 01:15:14,250
她因高烧在胡言乱语
She was delirious with fever.

1404
01:15:14,320 --> 01:15:16,780
所有的被褥都在地上  
All the bed covers were on the floor 

1405
01:15:16,780 --> 01:15:18,020
所有窗户大开
and the windows were wide open.

1406
01:15:18,130 --> 01:15:19,290
护士不在房间
The nurse wasn't in the room.

1407
01:15:19,360 --> 01:15:21,550
我赶紧尽快替母亲盖上被子
I ran and covered my mother up as quickly as I could.

1408
01:15:21,630 --> 01:15:24,360
此时我听见身后的开门声
Just then I heard a door open behind me.

1409
01:15:25,000 --> 01:15:26,860
护士站在那里
The nurse stood there.

1410
01:15:27,400 --> 01:15:31,030
她默不作声，但她的眼神
She didn't say a word, but there was a look in her eyes...

1411
01:15:31,210 --> 01:15:32,870
令我无法忘记
I'll never forget.

1412
01:15:34,940 --> 01:15:38,040
两天后，我母亲死了
Two days later, my mother was dead.

1413
01:15:41,350 --> 01:15:43,680
你知道那护士是谁？  
Do you know who that nurse was?

1414
01:15:43,880 --> 01:15:45,550
-不，谁？    -菲莉丝
No. Who? Phyllis.

1415
01:15:46,020 --> 01:15:48,390
我试图告诉爸爸，但那时我只是个孩子
I tried to tell my father, but I was just a kid then.

1416
01:15:48,460 --> 01:15:51,620
他不听我的，半年后，他们结婚了
He wouldn't listen to me. Six months later she married him...

1417
01:15:51,690 --> 01:15:54,210
我一直安慰自己说
and I kind of talked myself out of the idea 

1418
01:15:54,210 --> 01:15:56,100
她不会做那种事
she could have done anything like that.

1419
01:15:56,160 --> 01:15:58,940
但现在这感觉回来了  
But now it's all back again, 

1420
01:15:58,940 --> 01:16:00,620
现在我爸爸也出事了
now that something's happened to my father, too.

1421
01:16:00,700 --> 01:16:02,620
这么说没道理，迪崔克森小姐  
You're not making sense, Miss Dietrichson. 

1422
01:16:02,620 --> 01:16:04,540
你爸爸是摔下火车
Your father fell off a train.

1423
01:16:04,610 --> 01:16:06,220
对，他摔下火车两天前
Yes, and two days before he fell off that train, 

1424
01:16:06,220 --> 01:16:07,630
菲莉丝在干嘛？
what was Phyllis doing?

1425
01:16:07,710 --> 01:16:10,200
她在她房间面对镜子，头戴黑帽
She was in her room in front of a mirror, with a black hat on...

1426
01:16:10,280 --> 01:16:11,610
往上披一块黑纱
pinning a black veil to it.

1427
01:16:11,680 --> 01:16:15,080
好像她等不及要看自己服丧的样子
As if she couldn't wait to see how she would look in mourning.

1428
01:16:15,180 --> 01:16:17,210
您饱受打击，迪崔克森小姐
You've had a pretty bad shock, Miss Dietrichson.

1429
01:16:17,280 --> 01:16:18,910
这些事是不是你的想象？ 
Aren't you just imagining these things?

1430
01:16:19,020 --> 01:16:20,450
我在镜子里看到她的眼睛
I caught her eyes in the mirror.

1431
01:16:20,520 --> 01:16:23,550
有着我母亲死前有过的那种眼神
They had that look in them they had before my mother died.

1432
01:16:23,620 --> 01:16:25,110
一样的眼神
That same look.

1433
01:16:25,830 --> 01:16:27,590
你不喜欢你继母，是吗？  
You don't like your stepmother, do you?

1434
01:16:27,660 --> 01:16:29,490
是不是就因为她是继母？ 
Isn't it just because she is your stepmother?

1435
01:16:29,560 --> 01:16:32,000
我恨她是因为是她干的，她是为了钱
I loathe her because she did it. She did it for the money.

1436
01:16:32,070 --> 01:16:34,400
但你不会赔钱给她，是吗，奈夫先生？
Only you're not going to pay her, are you, Mr. Neff?

1437
01:16:34,470 --> 01:16:36,620
她这次没法逍遥法外  
She's not going to get away with it this time, 

1438
01:16:36,620 --> 01:16:37,600
因为我会揭发她
because I'm going to speak up.

1439
01:16:37,670 --> 01:16:39,160
我要将我知道的告诉大家
I'm going to tell everything I know.

1440
01:16:39,240 --> 01:16:41,160
你得小心，说这些事..  
You'd better be careful, saying things like... 

1441
01:16:41,160 --> 01:16:43,570
我不害怕，你看着吧
I'm not afraid. You'll see.

1442
01:16:51,890 --> 01:16:53,220
对不起
I'm sorry.

1443
01:16:56,590 --> 01:16:58,890
我不是有意这样的
I didn't mean to act like this.

1444
01:17:00,160 --> 01:17:03,220
你和我说过的这些，还和谁说过？  
All this that you've been telling me, who else have you told?

1445
01:17:03,300 --> 01:17:04,490
没人
No one.

1446
01:17:04,630 --> 01:17:07,120
-你的继母呢？   -当然没有
How about your stepmother? Of course not.

1447
01:17:08,100 --> 01:17:09,630
我搬出来了
I've moved out.

1448
01:17:10,740 --> 01:17:12,860
我不再住家里了
I'm not living at home anymore.

1449
01:17:12,940 --> 01:17:15,500
你还没告诉你男朋友吧？那个扎切提？ 
And you haven't told that boyfriend of yours? Zachetti?

1450
01:17:15,580 --> 01:17:18,480
我和他分了，我们吵架了
I'm not seeing him anymore. We had a fight.

1451
01:17:20,080 --> 01:17:21,910
你现在住哪？  
Where are you living now?

1452
01:17:21,980 --> 01:17:24,970
我在好莱坞有个小公寓
I got myself a little apartment in Hollywood.

1453
01:17:25,250 --> 01:17:28,220
四堵墙，你就那么呆坐着？  
Four walls, and you just sit and look at them?

1454
01:17:29,090 --> 01:17:30,580
是，奈夫先生
Yes, Mr. Neff.

1455
01:17:33,430 --> 01:17:34,950
于是那晚我带她去吃饭...
So that evening I took her to dinner...

1456
01:17:35,030 --> 01:17:36,860
去了没人会看见我们的...
at a Mexican restaurant down on 

1457
01:17:36,860 --> 01:17:38,690
奥尔韦拉街的一家墨西哥餐馆
Olvera Street where nobody would see us.

1458
01:17:38,770 --> 01:17:40,760
我想让她高兴
I wanted to cheer her up.

1459
01:17:41,170 --> 01:17:44,600
第二天是周日，我们开车去了海滩
The next day was Sunday and we went for a ride down to the beach.

1460
01:17:44,670 --> 01:17:47,400
她心情好了一点，甚至会笑
She had loosened up a bit, she was even laughing.

1461
01:17:47,470 --> 01:17:48,840
我得确保她
I had to make sure that 

1462
01:17:48,840 --> 01:17:51,040
不会将菲莉丝的那些事告诉别人
she wouldn't tell that stuff about Phyllis to anybody else.

1463
01:17:51,110 --> 01:17:54,050
那像炸药，无论真伪
It was dynamite, whether it was true or not.

1464
01:17:54,250 --> 01:17:56,080
而我没机会和菲莉丝交谈
And I had no chance to talk to Phyllis.

1465
01:17:56,150 --> 01:17:58,340
你像老鹰般盯着她，基斯
You were watching her like a hawk, Keyes.

1466
01:17:58,420 --> 01:18:00,450
我甚至不能打给她  
I couldn't even phone her 

1467
01:18:00,450 --> 01:18:02,750
因为我怕你会监听
because I was afraid you had the wires tapped.

1468
01:18:02,960 --> 01:18:05,170
周一早上我桌上有个便条  
Monday morning there was a note on my desk 

1469
01:18:05,170 --> 01:18:06,950
是你想见我，基斯
that you wanted to see me, Keyes.

1470
01:18:07,030 --> 01:18:10,000
闪念间我以为是萝拉的事
For a minute I wondered if it could be about Lola.

1471
01:18:10,060 --> 01:18:11,530
事实更糟
It was worse.

1472
01:18:12,100 --> 01:18:16,060
你门外是我世上最不愿见的人
Outside your door was the last guy in the world I wanted to see.

1473
01:18:25,210 --> 01:18:27,200
进来，进来，沃特
Come in. Come in, Walter.

1474
01:18:28,720 --> 01:18:31,620
-嗨，基斯。    -我想问你点事
Hello, Keyes. I want to ask you something.

1475
01:18:32,050 --> 01:18:33,920
既然我们相识多年...
After all the years we've known each other...

1476
01:18:33,990 --> 01:18:35,920
介意我来个直截了当的声明吗？ 
do you mind if I make a rather blunt statement?

1477
01:18:35,990 --> 01:18:37,580
-关于什么？     -关于我
About what? About me.

1478
01:18:38,190 --> 01:18:40,850
-沃特，我是个伟大的人。  -是吗？
Walter, I'm a very great man. Yeah?

1479
01:18:40,930 --> 01:18:43,690
迪崔克森的事，是谋杀...
This Dietrichson business, it's murder...

1480
01:18:43,760 --> 01:18:45,760
而谋杀不会天衣无缝
and murders don't come any neater.

1481
01:18:45,830 --> 01:18:48,700
一个毕生难逢的周密谋杀
As fancy a piece of homicide as anybody ever ran into...

1482
01:18:48,770 --> 01:18:51,030
聪明、狡猾、近乎完美，只是...
smart, tricky, almost perfect, but...

1483
01:18:51,940 --> 01:18:54,410
我想我已全部想通
I think Papa has it all figured out.

1484
01:18:54,470 --> 01:18:56,260
想通并用包装纸包裹
Figured out and wrapped up in tissue paper 

1485
01:18:56,260 --> 01:18:58,310
附加粉红蝴蝶结
with pink ribbons on it.

1486
01:18:58,380 --> 01:19:01,110
-继续说，我在听    -知道吗？
Go ahead. I'm listening. You know what?

1487
01:19:01,480 --> 01:19:04,420
迪崔克森就没上过火车
That guy Dietrichson was never on the train.

1488
01:19:05,590 --> 01:19:07,610
-他没有？     -没有
He wasn't? No, he wasn't.

1489
01:19:09,190 --> 01:19:11,490
你看，沃特，在时速15英里的火车上...
Now look, Walter. You can't be sure of killing a man...

1490
01:19:11,560 --> 01:19:14,690
将人推下，不确定就能杀死他
by throwing him off a train that's going 15 miles an hour.

1491
01:19:14,760 --> 01:19:17,230
唯一保险的办法是之前就杀死他
The only way you can be sure is to kill him first...

1492
01:19:17,300 --> 01:19:19,230
再将尸体丢在铁轨旁
and then throw his body on the tracks.

1493
01:19:19,300 --> 01:19:21,490
那就是说，要么在火车上杀他...
Now that would mean either killing him on the train...

1494
01:19:21,570 --> 01:19:22,500
要么...真正聪明之处就在这里，
or, and this is where it really gets fancy, 

1495
01:19:22,500 --> 01:19:25,300
你在别处杀了他...
you kill him somewhere else...

1496
01:19:25,370 --> 01:19:26,570
然后将他放在铁轨旁
and put him on the tracks.

1497
01:19:26,640 --> 01:19:29,910
两个可能性，我认为是第二个
Two possibilities, and I personally buy the second.

1498
01:19:31,140 --> 01:19:32,670
你比我厉害多了，基斯
You're way ahead of me, Keyes.

1499
01:19:32,780 --> 01:19:34,540
你看，沃特，是这样...
Well, look, Walter, it was like this.

1500
01:19:34,820 --> 01:19:38,480
他们杀掉那人，他妻子和某人...
They killed the guy, the wife and a somebody else...

1501
01:19:38,750 --> 01:19:40,560
然后那人拿着拐杖...  
and the somebody else took the crutches 

1502
01:19:40,560 --> 01:19:42,150
假扮迪崔克森先生上车...
and went on the train as Dietrichson...

1503
01:19:42,220 --> 01:19:43,990
然后那人跳车...
then the somebody else jumped off...

1504
01:19:44,060 --> 01:19:46,620
然后他们将尸体放在火车经过的铁轨旁
then they put the body on the tracks where the train had passed.

1505
01:19:46,690 --> 01:19:49,360
一次扮演，懂吗？易如反掌
An impersonation, see? A cinch to work.

1506
01:19:50,160 --> 01:19:52,290
因为当时是夜晚，很少有人
Because it was night, very few people were about...

1507
01:19:52,370 --> 01:19:53,890
他们忙着留意拐杖
they have the crutches to stare at...

1508
01:19:53,970 --> 01:19:56,440
反而留意不到人本身
they never really looked at the man at all.

1509
01:19:56,500 --> 01:19:58,660
是很周密，基斯，但可能有点太戏剧化了
Fancy all right, Keyes, but maybe it's a little too fancy.

1510
01:19:58,740 --> 01:20:02,110
是吗？告诉你，契合度就像手表齿轮
Is it? I tell you, it all fits together like a watch.

1511
01:20:02,780 --> 01:20:04,680
现在来看我们求证方面的王牌
Now let's see what we have in the way of proof.

1512
01:20:04,740 --> 01:20:06,080
唯一曾真正好好看过...
The only guy who really got a good look 

1513
01:20:06,080 --> 01:20:07,650
冒牌迪崔克森先生的人...
at this supposed Dietrichson...

1514
01:20:07,710 --> 01:20:09,840
就坐在我门外
is sitting right outside my office.

1515
01:20:09,920 --> 01:20:13,350
我费力将他从俄勒冈请来
I took the trouble to bring him down here from Oregon.

1516
01:20:15,090 --> 01:20:17,920
-进来，杰克逊先生    -好的，基斯先生
Come here, Mr. Jackson. Yes, sir, Mr. Keyes.

1517
01:20:18,020 --> 01:20:19,690
你的雪茄不错
These are fine cigars you smoke.

1518
01:20:19,760 --> 01:20:21,490
-一毛多一根    -就是这意思
Two for a quarter. That's what I said.

1519
01:20:21,560 --> 01:20:23,120
好了，你研究过照片吗？ 
Well, did you study those photographs?

1520
01:20:23,200 --> 01:20:25,220
是的，我仔细研究过
Yes, indeed. I studied them thoroughly.

1521
01:20:25,300 --> 01:20:27,130
-很彻底。    -你有结论了吗？  
Very thoroughly. Have you made up your mind?

1522
01:20:27,200 --> 01:20:29,190
基斯先生，我是个梅德福人，俄勒岗州梅德福
Mister Keyes, I'm a Medford man. Medford, Oregon.

1523
01:20:29,270 --> 01:20:31,430
在梅德福我们不着急下结论
Up in Medford we take our time making up our mind.

1524
01:20:31,510 --> 01:20:34,530
这里不是梅德福，这里是急得很，快说吧
Well, we're not in Medford now. We're in a hurry. Let's have it.

1525
01:20:34,610 --> 01:20:36,840
这是迪崔克森先生最近的照片？  
Are these photographs of the late Mr. Dietrichson?

1526
01:20:36,910 --> 01:20:37,900
是
Yes.

1527
01:20:38,450 --> 01:20:40,640
-那我的答案是不。  -什么意思，不？
Then my answer is no. What do you mean, no?

1528
01:20:40,710 --> 01:20:42,910
我是说，这不是火车上那人
I mean, this is not the man that was on the train.

1529
01:20:42,980 --> 01:20:44,180
你愿意发誓吗？  
Will you swear to that?

1530
01:20:44,250 --> 01:20:46,240
基斯先生，我是个梅德福人，俄勒岗州梅德福
Mr. Keyes, I'm a Medford man. Medford, Oregon.

1531
01:20:46,320 --> 01:20:48,690
开口无妄言，既非妄言，我当然愿意发誓
If I say it, I mean it. If I mean it, of course I'll swear it.

1532
01:20:48,760 --> 01:20:50,380
你看，沃特，这就是证据
There you are, Walter. There's your proof.

1533
01:20:50,460 --> 01:20:52,120
这是奈夫先生，我们的销售员
This is Mr. Neff, one of our salesmen.

1534
01:20:52,190 --> 01:20:54,180
幸会，奈夫先生，非常荣幸。
Pleased to meet you, Mr. Neff. Pleased, indeed.

1535
01:20:54,260 --> 01:20:55,630
-你好吗？    -很好，谢谢
How are you? Very fine, thank you.

1536
01:20:55,700 --> 01:20:58,060
-不能更好了。     -请坐，杰克逊先生
Never was better. Sit down, Mr. Jackson.

1537
01:20:58,130 --> 01:20:59,810
可以形容一下
Just how would you describe 

1538
01:20:59,810 --> 01:21:01,500
你在观景台看到的那人吗？
the man you saw on the observation platform?

1539
01:21:01,570 --> 01:21:04,300
我肯定他比较年轻
Well, I'm pretty sure he was a younger man...

1540
01:21:04,400 --> 01:21:07,370
比照片中人年轻10至15岁
about 10 or 15 years younger than the man in these photographs.

1541
01:21:07,440 --> 01:21:09,470
迪崔克森先生快50了，是吗，沃特？
Dietrichson was about 50, wasn't he, Walter?

1542
01:21:09,540 --> 01:21:11,940
保单上写的51岁
Fifty-one, according to the policy.

1543
01:21:12,010 --> 01:21:14,880
我看见的人绝对不像是51岁
The man I saw was nothing like 51 years old.

1544
01:21:15,120 --> 01:21:17,610
当然，观景台很昏暗
Of course, it was pretty dark out on that platform.

1545
01:21:17,680 --> 01:21:19,950
现在回想，他还刻意背对着我
Come to think of it, he tried to keep his back towards me.

1546
01:21:20,020 --> 01:21:22,650
-但我仍很肯定。   -谢谢你，杰克逊
But I'm positive just the same. Thank you, Jackson.

1547
01:21:22,720 --> 01:21:25,160
当然，你明白此事必须绝对保密吧？  
Of course, you understand this matter is strictly confidential?

1548
01:21:25,230 --> 01:21:26,460
我们在洛杉矶可能还需要你 
We may need you again down here in Los Angeles, 

1549
01:21:26,460 --> 01:21:28,320
如果要上法庭
if the case comes to court.

1550
01:21:28,400 --> 01:21:31,160
随时奉陪，我愿意为你效劳，先生们
Any time you need me, I'm entirely at your disposal, gentlemen.

1551
01:21:31,230 --> 01:21:34,530
-只要费用由你支付，当然      -哦，当然
Expenses paid, of course. Oh, yes. Yes. Of course.

1552
01:21:36,100 --> 01:21:38,730
找鲁宾，出纳部的
Get me Lubin, in the cashier's office.

1553
01:21:39,410 --> 01:21:41,470
喂，鲁宾，我是基斯
Hello, Lubin. This is Keyes.

1554
01:21:41,540 --> 01:21:44,370
听着，我现在让一个叫杰克逊的去你那
Listen. I'm sending a man named Jackson down to you 

1555
01:21:44,370 --> 01:21:45,640
带着报销单
with an expense account.

1556
01:21:45,710 --> 01:21:46,830
我们把他从俄勒冈梅德福找来，
Well, we brought him down here from Medford, 

1557
01:21:46,830 --> 01:21:48,510
是为了...
Oregon in connection with...

1558
01:21:48,580 --> 01:21:50,350
迪崔克森的案子
the Dietrichson claim.

1559
01:21:51,420 --> 01:21:53,550
支付他的酒店账单，好吗？
Well, take care of his hotel bill, will you?

1560
01:21:53,620 --> 01:21:54,710
去过俄勒冈吗，奈夫先生？ 
Ever been in Oregon, Mr. Neff?

1561
01:21:54,790 --> 01:21:55,810
是的，他马上下去
Yeah. He'll be right down.

1562
01:21:55,890 --> 01:21:57,410
没有，从没去过
No. Never been up there.

1563
01:21:57,620 --> 01:22:00,220
等等，你玩钓鳟鱼吗？  
Wait a minute. You go trout fishing?

1564
01:22:00,290 --> 01:22:03,960
-我也许在克拉马斯瀑布见过你     -不，我不钓鱼
Maybe I saw you up Klamath Falls way. Nope. I don't fish.

1565
01:22:04,260 --> 01:22:07,560
你不钓鱼，奈夫先生。奈夫...是这名字
You don't go fishing, Mr. Neff. Neff. It's the name.

1566
01:22:08,100 --> 01:22:10,700
-在科瓦利斯有个奈夫家族    -和我没关系
There's a family of Neffs in Corvallis. No relation.

1567
01:22:10,770 --> 01:22:13,170
我想想，那个奈夫是汽车经纪
Let me see. This man's an automobile dealer in Corvallis.

1568
01:22:13,240 --> 01:22:15,570
-听说也很受尊敬        -好了，杰克逊先生
A very reputable man, too, I'm told. All right, Mr. Jackson.

1569
01:22:15,640 --> 01:22:17,170
请去出纳部
Suppose you go down to the cashier's office.

1570
01:22:17,240 --> 01:22:18,710
11楼27室
Room 27 on the 11th floor.

1571
01:22:18,780 --> 01:22:20,550
他们会处理你的报销单
He'll take care of your expense account 

1572
01:22:20,550 --> 01:22:22,080
及今晚火车票
and your ticket for the train tonight.

1573
01:22:22,150 --> 01:22:23,140
今晚 ？ 
Tonight?

1574
01:22:23,250 --> 01:22:24,860
明早更好一些。
Tomorrow morning would suit me better. 

1575
01:22:24,860 --> 01:22:26,480
镇上有个很好的整骨疗法专家...
There's a very good osteopath in town...

1576
01:22:26,550 --> 01:22:29,350
-我走前想去看看     -整骨疗法专家？ 
I'd like to see before I leave. Osteopath?

1577
01:22:29,890 --> 01:22:32,950
好吧，只是这个不报销
Well, just don't put her on the expense account.

1578
01:22:33,860 --> 01:22:35,380
好了，再见，先生们
Well, goodbye, gentlemen.

1579
01:22:35,460 --> 01:22:37,760
幸会，再见
It's been a pleasure. Goodbye.

1580
01:22:40,070 --> 01:22:42,280
太好了，沃特  
There it is, Walter. 

1581
01:22:42,280 --> 01:22:44,000
纸快包不住火了
It's beginning to come apart at the seams already.

1582
01:22:44,070 --> 01:22:46,800
没有完美的谋杀，早晚会露馅
Murder's never perfect. Always comes apart sooner or later.

1583
01:22:46,870 --> 01:22:49,340
若有两人参与，一般会早露馅
And when two people are involved, it's usually sooner.

1584
01:22:49,410 --> 01:22:52,310
现在，我们知道迪崔克森太太参与了，还有一个人
Now, we know the Dietrichson dame is in it, and a somebody else.

1585
01:22:52,380 --> 01:22:54,400
很快就会知道那人是谁
Pretty soon we'll know who that somebody else is.

1586
01:22:54,480 --> 01:22:55,680
他会出现，一定会的
He'll show. He's got to show. 

1587
01:22:55,680 --> 01:22:57,350
他们总要在某时某处见面
Sometime, somewhere, they've got to meet.

1588
01:22:57,420 --> 01:22:58,710
他们将情绪激动
Their emotions are all kicked up.

1589
01:22:58,790 --> 01:23:00,420
是爱是恨并不重要  
Whether it's love or hate doesn't matter. 

1590
01:23:00,420 --> 01:23:02,220
他们无法保持距离
They can't keep away from each other.

1591
01:23:02,290 --> 01:23:04,760
他们可能以为两人参与就会双倍安全
They may think it's twice as safe because there are two of them.

1592
01:23:04,820 --> 01:23:06,220
但不会双倍安全
But it isn't twice as safe.

1593
01:23:06,290 --> 01:23:09,460
而是二十倍危险。他们犯下谋杀罪...
It's 10 times twice as dangerous. They've committed a murder...

1594
01:23:09,530 --> 01:23:11,660
而这不像一起乘电车...
and it's not like taking a trolley ride together...

1595
01:23:11,730 --> 01:23:13,490
可以在不同站下车
where they can get off at different stops.

1596
01:23:13,570 --> 01:23:15,830
他们被捆在一起一路前行
They're stuck with each other and they've got to ride...

1597
01:23:15,900 --> 01:23:17,370
直至到达终点
all the way to the end of the line.

1598
01:23:17,440 --> 01:23:19,770
而这是一趟单程，终站是坟墓
And it's a one-way trip, and the last stop is the cemetery.

1599
01:23:19,840 --> 01:23:21,640
她已经申请索赔
She put in her claim.

1600
01:23:22,280 --> 01:23:24,870
我将会扔回给她
I'm gonna throw it right back at her.

1601
01:23:30,450 --> 01:23:32,210
如果她敢，尽管告我们
Let her sue us if she dares.

1602
01:23:32,290 --> 01:23:35,080
我静待她和那个人
I'll be ready for her and that somebody else.

1603
01:23:35,160 --> 01:23:37,680
他们会一起自掘坟墓
They'll be digging their own graves.

1604
01:23:46,130 --> 01:23:48,790
迪崔克森太太？这里是杰利店
Mrs. Dietrichson? This is Jerry's Market.

1605
01:23:48,870 --> 01:23:50,770
您需要的英国肥皂
We just got in a shipment of that English soap 

1606
01:23:50,770 --> 01:23:51,860
刚刚到货了
you were asking about.

1607
01:23:51,940 --> 01:23:55,500
您今天来取吗？谢谢，迪崔克森太太
Will you be coming by today? Thank you, Mrs. Dietrichson.

1608
01:24:22,570 --> 01:24:25,200
-嗨，沃特    -过来
Hello, Walter. Come over here.

1609
01:24:28,910 --> 01:24:31,840
-什么事？  -出大事了
What's the matter? Everything's the matter.

1610
01:24:33,880 --> 01:24:35,210
基斯要拒绝你的索赔
Keyes is rejecting your claim.

1611
01:24:35,280 --> 01:24:36,480
他虎视眈眈等着
He's sitting back with his mouth watering, 

1612
01:24:36,480 --> 01:24:37,880
等待你提出控告
waiting for you to sue.

1613
01:24:37,950 --> 01:24:39,750
他希望你提出，但你不可以
He wants you to sue, but you're not going to.

1614
01:24:39,820 --> 01:24:42,720
-他凭什么阻止我？    -凭很多
What's he got to stop me? He's got plenty.

1615
01:24:45,590 --> 01:24:46,960
他弄清了事发过程
He's figured out how it was worked.

1616
01:24:47,030 --> 01:24:48,820
知道火车上的是另有其人
He knows it was somebody else on the train...

1617
01:24:48,900 --> 01:24:50,730
还挖到一个可以作证的目击者
and he's dug up a witness he thinks can prove it.

1618
01:24:50,800 --> 01:24:53,160
怎么证明？ 如果他拒绝赔偿，我就提出控告
Prove it how? If he rejects that claim, I have to sue.

1619
01:24:53,230 --> 01:24:55,330
是吗 ？然后你就得上法庭...
Yeah? And then you're in court 

1620
01:24:55,330 --> 01:24:56,730
很多其他事就会浮出水面
and a lot of other things are going to come up.

1621
01:24:56,800 --> 01:25:00,640
例如，关于你和首任迪崔克森太太
Like, for instance, about you and the first Mrs. Dietrichson.

1622
01:25:00,810 --> 01:25:02,640
我和首任迪崔克森太太怎么了？  
